title: louise's noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown up meat and drain.
In large casserole mix together all ingredients.
Top with parmesan and mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: corn medley
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in pan. Cook and stir over medium heat until butter is melted. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes. Stir in tomato and sugar or sugar substitute. Cook, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Yields 5 servings.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Heat syrup, butter and chocolate chips to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together oleo and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine with oatmeal.
Add to rest of ingredients. Dough will be stiff.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli and cauliflower. cut up and set aside. Add onion, eggs, cheese and bacon; mix together. Mix salad dressing, vinegar and sugar. Pour over other ingredients. Chill.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and pat dry mushrooms.
Remove stems and finely chop. Melt margarine in a large skillet; saute chopped stems, celery, onion and savory.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, beaten egg yolk, salt and pepper.
Place mushrooms, cavity side up, in a greased baking dish.
Fill cavities with stuffing mixture; sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple raisin snacks
directions: Combine oats, flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: owens chinese stuffed dumplings
directions: Combine soy sauce and cornstarch, then thoroughly mix all of the first 5 ingredients.
Spread the 24 wrappers on a work surface. Separate the sausage mixture into 24 portions.
With a brush, moisten one side of a wrapper.
Place a portion of the stuffing in it, fold the wrapper into a triangle and seal the edges.
Continue until all are done.
A multi-layer steamer is the perfect utensil in which to steam these morsels.
If you are using a bamboo steamer, place water into the wok until it is an inch from the bottom of the steamer.
Heat the water to a boil.
Remove the steamer from the wok.

Oil the bottom of each steamer tray and fill each tray with the dumplings, making sure that they do not touch. Return stacked trays to the wok and steam for 10 to 12 minutes. Gently remove the dumplings from the trays and arrange around bowls of hot garlic oil and soy sauce for dipping.

title: mexican luncheon
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Use 3/4 teaspoon per mug of hot water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add zucchini and nuts last.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into pans and bake for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain onions and squash.
Mix soup and sour cream; fold into squash and onions.
Mix stuffing mix and melted butter. Place 1/2 of stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with squash mixture.
Put rest of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Stir into mixture until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice or dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Mix the ketchup and cognac and slowly add the cream until the mixture is a pale pink.
Mix in the paprika.
Add the shrimp and mushrooms.
Serve in cocktail glasses with a slice of lemon.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add all other ingredients in order.
Cover and freeze.
Thaw about 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in oblong pan.
Punch holes and pour pineapple and juice on cake.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; add vanilla. Pour into cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Cover cake with cream cheese and pudding mixture, then put whipped topping on that.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add beans and heat.
Combine salsa and sauce.
Add to meat mixture, about 1/3 of it.
Heat.
Roll meat mixture in tortillas.
Place, seam side down, into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Pour remaining sauce down the middle of the tortillas.
Grate cheese and sprinkle down the middle on top of sauce.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and edges of tortillas are brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in bowl at room temperature for 1 hour.
Put in covered container and refrigerate. Will keep good
in refrigerator.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water with parsley flakes, salt and pepper until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Debone and remove skin.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add melted oleo; stir in nuts, raisins, coconut and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing, cheese and Salad Supreme.
Cook and rinse spaghetti with cold water; drain well.
Add cut up vegetables and pour dressing over.
Mix well.
Make 1 or 2 days ahead.

title: aunt gloria's roll out cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, vanilla and half and half.
Combine flour, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
To flour mixture add 2 cups oleo.
Mix like a pie crust.
When all mixed together, add wet mixture.
After adding wet mixture, try to roll out.
If sticky, add more flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Cool in the refrigerator.
Roll out and bake at 350°.

title: deluxe marbled brownies
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and 2 cups sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in 2 teaspoons vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine 1 1/3 cups flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture; blend well.
Spread half into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cream remaining butter and cream cheese in a small bowl.
Add remaining sugar and flour; blend well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter in pan.
Spread remaining batter over cream cheese mixture.
Gently swirl with knife for marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: barbecued corn on the cob
directions: Wrap pieces of bacon around each ear of corn.
Then wrap tightly with aluminum foil.
Prick each piece with a fork a few times and place on a very hot grill.
Turn a couple of times to ensure complete doneness.
When completely done, remove foil and enjoy both corn and bacon, if desired.
This is a great way to excite your taste buds!

title: diet food cool whip
directions: Put water
and	lemon juice in a bowl and add dry milk. Beat until stiff.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Chill.

title: mojadas(colombian style cheese biscuits)
directions: Mix together and add enough water (about 1 cup) to make a dough.
Roll dough in balls about the size of golf balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: virginia cotton's old fashion tea cakes
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl. Add eggs, 2/3 cup lard, milk, soda, powder and vanilla.
Knead.
Add additional 2/3 cup lard.
Knead well.
Roll a portion of dough very thin and sprinkle with sugar. Cut out and bake quickly in hot oven.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, soda and cereal.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix with a spoon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Will also need 6 paper muffin liner cups.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix 4 egg yolks with sugar in saucepan.
Add 1 quart milk and pinch of salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Place cooled mixture in ice cream freezer container.
Add pudding, evaporated milk, beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Mix well and fill container with milk.
Freeze ice cream.

title: two cup cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat well with wire whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of the cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze firm about 4 hours.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers, if desired.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend all ingredients in a food processor or mixing bowl until light pink in color.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top (I like Duncan Hines golden butter cake).
Top with 1 1/2 cups chopped walnuts.
Pour 3/4 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Divide whipped topping among 10 dessert glasses using about 1/3 cup in each.
With back of spoon, make a depression in center and spread topping up sides of the glasses.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package for pudding.
Spoon into glasses.
Chill.

title: old fashioned pound cake(may prepare ahead.)
directions: Prepare batter and bake cake in 10-inch tube pan according to package directions; cool well, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cake from pan.
Cut a 1-inch slice crosswise from top of cake and set aside.
Make cuts 1 inch from center and 1 inch from side of cake. With fingers, carefully remove cake within cuts, leaving a 1-inch base.
Reserve cake pieces.

title: never fail pie dough
directions: Mix well and chill.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Place
cocoa, sugar, flour, 1 1/2 cups milk and salt in microwave
for
minutes.
Stir and put it in another 2 minutes. Remove
and
add beaten egg yolks, 1/2 cup milk, butter and vanilla.
Place
back in microwave and cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes, until thick, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour pie mixture into baked pie crust.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together, put in 13x9 dish, freeze.
Cut into squares to serve. Keep frozen.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water until dissolved.
Add cold water and rest of ingredients.
Mix well and set in refrigerator to chill.
May be served with whipped cream.
Real good served with meat.

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup margarine in water until potatoes are nearly done.
Then add corn, milk and 1/4 cup margarine.
Simmer until done.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix in margarine thoroughly.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cafe-au-lait-squares
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle envelopes of gelatin over cold milk; let stand 1 minute and add hot coffee, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients until chocolate is melted. Pour into 8 or 9-inch square pan and chill to firm.
Cut 1-inch squares.

title: first-ever one dish meal for beginning cooks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Finely chop onion, garlic and celery. Saute in greased dish in microwave 2 minutes (if cooktop is used, saute until limp but not brown; stir constantly).
Add vegetables and tomato sauce.
Brown ground meat.
Drain off grease.
Mix vegetables and meat.
Put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake in oven until biscuits are done.

title: cheese dip in a crock-pot
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cut cheese in chunks and add to the mixture.
Ready when the cheese melts.
Serve over nacho chips.
Makes a lot.
(Do not try to keep this warm in the crock-pot because the cheese will stick to the crock-pot.)

title: apple pastry
directions: Mix first four ingredients like pie crust.
Separate egg.
To the yolk add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Roll 1/2 dough out in a rectangle to fit in a jelly roll pan.
Cover dough with apples. Over apples sprinkle mixture of sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and tapioca (if you don't have tapioca, add 2 more tablespoons flour.
Cover with second half of rolled out dough. Beat egg white slightly.
Brush over crust. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grape cream cheese pie
directions: Combine grapes and 3/4 cup sugar in pan. Dissolve cornstarch and water.
Gently stir into grape mixture.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and 1 tablespoon sugar. Coat bottom of graham cracker crust.
Remove grape mixture from heat. Stir in lemon juice. Cool. Fill pie shell with cooled pie mix.
Mix sour cream with 1 tablespoon sugar and vanilla. Spread over top of pie. Cool in refrigerator.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Combine hot chocolate chips, sugar and water; stir until smooth.
Beat egg yolks; add to chocolate and set aside.
Beat egg whites; fold into chocolate, whipped cream, vanilla and nuts. Fold.
Break up cake and put into pan layer with sauce, cake and sauce.
Cool several hours before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown.
Drain well.
Spread bread pieces in buttered casserole dish and top with sausage and cheese. Combine eggs, milk and seasoning; beat well and pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set and does not shake easy.

title: potato hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: salmon ball
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well with hands and shape into ball. Roll in crushed pecans or walnuts. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: aunt edna's recipe
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
In a saucepan with pineapple juice from chunks.
Mix egg, salt, flour and sugar; bring to a boil while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Pour over contents in bowl.
Let chill.
Serves 10.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine beef, tomatoes, garlic, onions, tomato paste and bay leaves.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add parsley and basil; simmer for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Shred Mozzarella cheese.
Combine egg and Ricotta, salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Alternate sauce with lasagna noodles and cheese mixture in greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Will serve 12 people.

title: chocolate covered buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Melt chocolate chips.
Add 1/3 stick paraffin to chocolate until paraffin is melted.
Let cool a few minutes.
Form first mixture into balls.
Using a toothpick, dip balls into chocolate mixture. Place on waxed paper and chill.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Marinate chicken 1/2 hour in 1 tablespoon oil, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.

title: quick chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Sift together salt, sugar and flour.
In a saucepan bring to a boil the butter or margarine, water, Crisco, buttermilk and cocoa; remove.
Cool and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and add eggs and soda.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, longer for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost while hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli; blanch and coarsely chop.
Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 350° in a pan of water.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and spread in bottom of oblong dish. Sprinkle about 1/2 cup powdered sugar over graham crackers.
Cream butter with 2 cups powdered sugar.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and mix with butter and sugar.
Pour over crackers.
Next layer sliced bananas, then pineapple, then drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Last sprinkle chopped nuts over top and then place cherries all over the cake.
Do not cook.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: old-fashioned white bread
directions: Heat milk and butter to 120° (or lukewarm).
Add sugar and salt. Stir until dissolved.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and yeast, then the warmed liquids and mix well (only add about 1/2 of the flour at this time).
Gradually add remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead dough on well floured surface until smooth and satiny (3 to 5 minutes).
Place into buttered bowl and allow to rise in a warm place until double in size (covered). Punch down and place on floured surface.
Knead for 2 minutes
and divide dough into equal parts and shape accordingly (rolls, bread, etc.).
Place into buttered pans and allow dough to rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Butter top while warm. Makes 2 loaves or 24 rolls. Enjoy!

title: maple apple crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and put in ungreased glass baking dish (8 x 12-inch) or 9-inch pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and spread on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Serves 12.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix in heavy pan on low heat.
Cook until it boils and thickens.
Let cool.
Good over fresh fruit.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cheese taters
directions: Quarter potatoes and set in ice water for 30 minutes.
In bag, mix other ingredients (except butter).
Put potatoes in bag and shake until coated.
Put butter in baking dish and melt.
Add potatoes.
Bake at 450° to 500°, turning occasionally until done and brown.

title: pecan breakfast bread
directions: Separate each roll, and butter it.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Sprinkle over each roll.
Roll from wide end to point. Place in a greased 9 x 5 loaf pan, forming 2 layers.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until deep brown. Remove from pan at once.
Place right side up.
Drizzle with topping.

title: teriyaki flank steak
directions: Combine all the ingredients and pour into a Ziploc bag with one or two flank steaks.
Marinate overnight and barbecue.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Dice and drain all fruit except strawberries.
Combine in a 2-quart casserole; set aside.
Boil water; add sugar, boil until clear.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Freeze overnight.
Set out 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Cut in squares (can also be poured into muffin tins with paper liners to make individual servings). Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Bring macaroni to boil, cook until tender and drain.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice (should be creamy).
Open tuna and drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix macaroni (elbows), salad dressing and tuna.
Chill for 3 hours and serve cold.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Follow pudding directions and spread over cake.
Over this scatter pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.
Top each serving with a cherry.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and put into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan.
Melt the stick of butter, saving a small amount to place on top.
Place shrimp over top of crushed crackers; pour butter over shrimp and crackers.
Pour the white wine over mixture.
Pour remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for about 3/4 of an hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add oats and mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Deep-fry until golden brown.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Rinse wild rice in cold water; drain.
Cook rice in chicken stock until tender (25 to 30 minutes).
In a separate pan, cook and stir celery, onion, mushrooms, carrots and garlic in butter until tender.
Add flour and cook; stir 1 to 2 minutes.
Add chicken stock with rice, salt, curry powder, pepper and pimento. Mixture can be refrigerated at this point for later use.
To serve, heat soup mixture.
Stir in half and half, checking for consistency.
Serve hot.
Garnish with slivered almonds.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar-pecan crisps
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in flour.
Shape dough into 2 rolls, each about 1 1/2 inches in diameter and 6 inches long.
Roll each in 1/4 cup of the pecans to coat outside.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill thoroughly.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Marinate first 5 ingredients for 30 minutes, covered, in the refrigerator.
Add 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt.
Beat 2 eggs in a bowl; place flour in another bowl.
Dip chicken pieces first in egg, then in flour.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Place in an ovenproof dish.
Add 1/2 cup cashews and 1/4 cup green onion tops.
Keep warm in a 250° oven while making sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar until thick and yellow.
Add zucchini; mix well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hermits (bar cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Slowly add to creamed mixture, lastly adding raisins and chopped walnuts.
Make 6 strips on cookie sheets (2 strips per sheet).
Bake at 375° for approximately 9 minutes.

title: surprise sandwich loaf
directions: Slice bread into 16 even slices, but not all the way through. Butter bread slices, if desired.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, juices and sugar. Refrigerate. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together; put in greased baking dish.
Top with crushed chips and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: potluck dinner potato casserole
directions: Peel, quarter and boil potatoes until barely tender.
Drain, cool and grate on large side of grater (or lightly mash).
In large bowl, gently mix all ingredients, except butter.
Place mixture in greased, shallow pan.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
If made day before, add butter just before baking.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Heat 1 inch water to boiling.
Add cauliflower and broccoli. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook 5 minutes; drain. Rinse under cold water, drain.
Rinse peas under running cold water to separate; drain.
Mix mayo, yogurt, lemon juice, salt and pepper in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Toss. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Stir in tomatoes.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and wash.
Add Wish-Bone dressing and 1/2 bottle Salad Seasons.
Mix and marinate overnight.
Add bell pepper, onion, tomatoes and meat.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in cool whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Garnish with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate and oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Reserving 1/2 cup, press remaining oat mixture on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut.
Keeps well frozen.
Makes 36 bars.

title: dipped shortbread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter and vanilla; mix until thoroughly blended.
Shape into 1-inch thick logs; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Roll between palms of hands or on board into 2-inch fingers.
Bake at 350° on ungreased sheet for 10 to 12 minutes; cool.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate pieces and shortening; remove from heat.
Dip in cookies; roll in nuts or sprinkles.
Place on waxed paper tray; chill until chocolate is firm (about 1 hour).
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion in large frypan.
Cook noodles as directed on package in medium boiler while meat is browning.
Drain meat to remove fat.
Return meat to heat, add tomato sauce, can tomatoes and chili mix, cook to blend ingredients.
Drain water from noodles.
Layer noodles, meat mix, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Keep layering.
If necessary, repeat layering.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool some and cut in squares.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water, but do not add cold water. Stir in sherbet until melted.
Add mandarin oranges and juice. Let set in refrigerator.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 5 minutes; reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: chicken barrettini(serves 4.  approximate preparation and cooking time: 35 minutes)
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in a large skillet.
Saute chicken breasts in margarine, cooking at medium heat about 3 minutes a side.
Remove chicken breasts from skillet and store in a covered dish for warmth.
Leave fat and crumbles in skillet.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and 1/2 cup Marsala wine, stirring as they are added. Heat until just short of boiling.
Then add garlic salt, oregano and tarragon leaves.
Stir to assure good distribution.
Then simmer for about 3 minutes.
Then add onion, green pepper and straw mushrooms, stirring as you add.
Cut heat to simmer and let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Insinuate the cornstarch dissolved in water, stirring broadly as you add.
Raise heat to high and cook until mixture thickens and is bubbly.
Reduce heat and simmer once more. Add the cayenne pepper and stir strongly, to assure good distribution in the mix.
Stir and cook until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Re-introduce chicken breasts.
Cover and let simmer for about 12 minutes, turning once every 3 minutes and basting the breasts with the sauce.
Remove chicken from skillet and place on serving dish.
Garnish, if desired, with parsley and/or lemon slices.
(Garnish after covering the chicken with the sauce, on serving dish.)

title: fish chowder
directions: In a large pot, saute salt pork until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon, save.
Add onion, saute until soft.
Add potatoes and salt to pot.
Add enough water to cover for about 15 minutes. Add fish and simmer until easily flaked with 2 prong fork into large pieces and until cooked.
Add milk and pork cubes, correct seasonings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on box.
Drain.
In a large dish put a layer of macaroni, layer of cheese, several pats of butter, salt and pepper and a small amount of milk.
Continue layers until all ingredients have been used, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: marble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and syrup.
Pour batter into pan by thirds and pour syrup and chips between layers of batter. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Combine artichoke, chili peppers, cheese and mayo.
Turn into an 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix eggs, butter (melt), milk, flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over corn.
Mix well.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no mess lasagne
directions: Pour 1 cup spaghetti sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of noodles.
Spread half of ground chuck on top of noodles, then sprinkle garlic powder, salt, pepper and half of onion.
Spoon on half of cottage cheese, then some American cheese.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce.
Repeat, using rest of ingredients. Pour on 2 cups spaghetti sauce.
Press down; pour on hot water gently over top.
Press down again.
Cover with foil.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Brown margarine in a skillet.
Add brown sugar and 4 tablespoons canned milk.
Cook to a taffy.
In a 2 to 3-quart double boiler pan beat egg yolks (set aside whites for meringue) and thicken with cornstarch.
Add 3 cups milk and vanilla.
Stir in mixture from skillet and cook until thick.
Stir constantly. Cool.
Put into baked 10-inch pastry crust; top with meringue. Brown meringue in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Put the Starter in a large mixing bowl.
Scald milk and add sugar, shortening and salt.
When cool, add to the starter.
Place dough in a greased bowl.
Brush top lightly with melted shortening. Cover with a cloth and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Punch down; let rise until double.
Roll into a ball.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into a loaf and place in loaf pan.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat.
In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper together well.
Pour mixture over crab meat and fold in lightly but thoroughly.
Form into six cakes.
Saute in butter for 3 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Knead well.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with butter and top with another circle.
Let raise for 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust(3 crusts)
directions: Cut flour, shortening and salt together.
Add cold water, egg and vinegar.
Mix together.
Roll out and bake as recipe directs.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans with butter flavor Crisco.
Flour lightly.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, sugar, eggs, grated lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.

Add to batter alternately with milk at low speed. Beat until batter is smooth after each addition; pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 58 to 62 minutes, or until deep golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on cooling rack for 20 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto rack; cool completely. Makes 2 loaves.

title: beignets
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl. Add milk and egg and mix well. Drop into deep heated fat by the spoonful. Grease should be at least 375°. Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: jennings' 100th year ole fruit cake
directions: Soak fruit with jelly overnight.
Add 2 beaten eggs, pecans, sugar, raisins and butter to fruit and jelly mixture.
Separately sift together dry ingredients, mixing well.
Then add to fruit mixtures.
If necessary, add more flour to desired consistency.

title: black bottom ice cream pie
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Pat into bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.

Freeze while preparing chocolate sauce and filling. Melt chocolate in cream over low heat, stirring occasionally. When melted and thoroughly blended, remove from heat, add vanilla and chill until thickened.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, remove skins and grate.
Melt butter in double boiler.
Put in cheese, small amount at a time. Add onions, sour cream and milk.
Combine with potatoes.
Put in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: "catfish" slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Best slaw for a good old southern catfish fry.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Add flour and seasoning.
Stir in sour cream.
Add pimento and green beans.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Cut up apples and mix with sugar in a large bowl.
Sift all the dry ingredients and blend with apples and sugar.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Smooth over.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 400° for 15 minutes, or until brown.
Makes about 50.

title: winter mush
directions: Boil 2 quarts water in pot.
When it begins to boil, take meal with a spoon a little at a time and sprinkle meal in water while boiling.
Put a dash of salt in the water.
Stir until meal begins to thicken.
Test to see if thick enough.
Get a small bowl of sweet milk and put some of the mush in it and serve.
Put sugar in if desired.
Nourishing on a cold day.
Also it can be sliced and fried if desired.

title: curried steak
directions: Brown steak and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Place onion slices over meat.
Mix together all remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Crumble cooked bacon over broccoli; add cheese, onion and tomatoes. In separate bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Add to broccoli mixture and toss.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything together. Boil for 1/2 hour.
You can add more cayenne pepper to make hotter.
Great on spareribs or pork chops.

title: lasagne
directions: Lightly brown ground beef, onion and garlic in frying pan; drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper; cook slowly, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix cottage cheese and nutmeg. Spread 1 cup of meat sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan, place pineapple in bottom of pan, then layer pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix evenly on top, next layer pecans, then cut sticks of butter into 1/4 pats cover top of pecans.
Finally top with brown sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350.

title: creamed onions
directions: Place 10 onions on a rack over water in a saucepan.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Run under cold water and peel.

title: dave's baked barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Mix these and all the other ingredients together in a large baking dish or pot.
Cook until it boils, then bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine. Add brown sugar and cream together. Cook a few minutes until hot and bubbly. Then add 10x sugar. Beat well to cool.

title: sausage-vegetable casserole
directions: Cut
sausage into 1/2 inch slices.
Mix water, milk and sauce package
from
potato mix.
Add potato slices, sausage, peas and carrots and onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: brown sugar refrigerator rolls
directions: Roll chilled dough 1/4 inch thick on a floured board.
Spread with soft butter, then mixture made of brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped walnut meats.
Roll as for chocolate roll and cut dough in 1-inch pieces.
Place cut side down in a large buttered muffin pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover and let rise until double the size, about 2 hours.
Bake in a moderately hot oven.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cornmeal, salt and milk together and cook into a thin mush.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat eggs well.
Add yeast and eggs to the cooled mush mixture.
Add flour.
Knead into a soft dough.
Let dough rise until double in bulk.
Shape into rolls and bake at 375° until golden.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans over bottom of 10 x 14-inch cake pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Spoon over nuts and coconut mixture.
Cream the cheese, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st layer: Graham cracker crust.

title: ratatouille
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Cut unpeeled eggplant into squares.
Slice onion and peppers.
Saute onions in plenty of oil until soft.
Add peppers, then eggplant.
Ten minutes later, add tomatoes.
Simmer, covered for 15 minutes and uncovered for 15 more.
Good hot or cold.
Goes well with roast lamb and noodles.

title: onion beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, flour, onion soup mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add macaroni, then pour in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: lemon mint tea
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add tea bag, lemon drops, and mint leaves.
Turn off heat. Leave mixture to steep until cool.
Remove tea bag and mint leaves.
Serve over ice.

title: savory shrimp
directions: Slit peeled shrimp down center to butterfly leaving tails on. Remove veins.
Place butter in a bowl; mix in rest of ingredients to blend completely.
Put shrimp on a shallow broiling pan.
Place a dab of butter mixture on each shrimp.
Broil about 5 minutes. Makes about 6 servings.

title: peggy's sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into balls.
Cook at 425° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Season chicken with Season-All and black pepper.
Put in casserole dish.
Slice garlic on top of chicken.
Put melted butter over chicken.
Broil on high for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water. Place in a large bowl; add remaining ingredients and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight. Yield: 12-14 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Then chop and add cheese, soup, eggs, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well and place in buttered baking dish.
Mix melted butter and crushed Ritz crackers; sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until top is bubbly and brown.
Double or half as needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Clean chicken and cut into serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown onion in olive oil and add chicken.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Add tomatoes, carrots, celery, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: chococonut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage, milk and salt in a tightly covered pan.
Steam cabbage until tender when tried with a fork.
In a small jar, pour 4 tablespoons water. Add 3 tablespoons flour.
Place cover on jar and shake mixture until smooth.
Stir butter and flour and water thickening into cabbage.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring well.
Yields 5 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Sift sugar. Cream together sugar and butter until fluffy. Add flour, baking powder, milk, salt, extract and rind. Flour fruit in a little extra flour. Add to mix. Add nuts. Grease tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, salt, spices, milk and eggs; beat. Sift flour with soda and add to sugar mixture.
Add to nuts and raisins.
Bake at 375° or 400° until brown.

title: summertime pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and orange juice until smooth, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/4 cup lemon juice and lemon rind. Cool completely.
Fold in 6 cups of assorted fresh fruit.
Turn into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.

title: oven-fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish. Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Lay half of bread in greased pan (13 x 9-inch).
Put cheese and ham on top of bread.
Cover with rest of the bread.
Mix everything else except corn flakes and butter.
Pour mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir corn flakes into melted oleo next day.
Sprinkle over top of sandwiches.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In food processor, process sugar with orange rind until fine (about 1 minute).
Add butter and process until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and process until blended. Add yogurt, baking soda and nutmeg.
Process.
Sprinkle pecan and flour over mixture gradually and process briefly.
Place batter in greased muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding cheese cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 large Cool Whip.
When crust is cooled, spread with cheese mixture.
Mix Jell-O pudding with milk; pour over cheese layer.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Cool until firm; keep refrigerated.

title: butter pecan pie squares
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/3 cup sugar in a medium bowl; cut in 1/2 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press mixture evenly into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening and eggs until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
On piece of wax paper, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown. Add wine, green onions and parsley to remaining melted butter. When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce mixture around and over.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serve with sauce spooned over.
Yield: 4 half breasts.

title: aunt laura's famous chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back.

title: play dough for children
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and gradually add water and oil.
Cook over medium heat until warm.
Remove and add food coloring as desired.
Knead until solid.
Store in closed container.

title: pea salad
directions: 1. Drain peas and place in suitable mixing bowl.
2. Dice cheese and sweet pickles and add to peas.
3. Add 2-4 Tbsp. mayonaise and spices to taste.
4. Mix and chill.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together in a large bowl.
In a pan on stove, bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Add sour cream, eggs and soda.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir well.
Line shell with berries. Pour cooked mixture over strawberries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, brown first four ingredients in shortening; add salt.
Stir in water and bring to a boil.
Add spaghetti, broken into 2-inch pieces.
Cook uncovered 12 to 15 minutes; stir in tomatoes and ketchup.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken until tender and chop.
Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Place all ingredients in large cooker and simmer.
Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese on top of each bowl of soup.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add onion to hamburger meat in large skillet.
Brown and drain.
Prepare rice according to instructions on package.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Add corn, soup, grated cheese and hamburger mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, sprinkle some cheese on top and for color you can sprinkle on some paprika.

title: creamy beef and macaroni
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, macaroni and mayo; heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a covered casserole at 275° for 4 hours or in a crock-pot, set at low, for 4 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Simmer stew meat in water. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until meat is tender.

title: country-style steak
directions: Flour and salt meat, then brown on both sides in frying pan. Drain meat on paper towel, then put in crock-pot.
With meat drippings in frying pan, put flour to make gravy.
Add soup and 1 can of water and after gravy thickens, pour over meat.
Add onion. Let cook on high for 1 hour or until meat is tender or on low all day.

title: potato vegetable lasagna
directions: Optional:
Can use fresh veggies, partially cooked in microwave, instead of frozen ones.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Beat well until smooth.
Add eggs. Add vanilla, flour and cocoa.
Blend.
Fold in nuts and coconut. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Spread over hot cake 1 jar marshmallow cream.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla, lemon juice, salt and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling or your favorite topping.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; mix.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat just enough to mix together.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Mix and place in greased pan.
Mix rest of chips with confectioners sugar and as much cinnamon as desired.
Sprinkle on top of cake batter before baking.
Place in 350° preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fill each muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake in a 475° oven until golden brown.
Muffin tins do not need to be greased.
Yields 24 biscuits.

title: ada style pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in flour and brown in olive oil in cast iron skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir in tomato paste, boiling water and cooking wine.
Add lemon rind, cracked pepper and salt.
Bring to a boil.
More water and wine can be added if sauce does not cover meat.
Cover and lower heat to simmer until tender, 2 hours or
more.
Even better if cooked, refrigerated overnight and reheated!!
Serve with saffron rice.

title: paul's shrimp wraps
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute in butter the onions, celery and mushrooms.
Cook broccoli.
Melt cheese and soup.
Put all together with a dash of Tabasco sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients well except for flour.
Add flour to mixture.
Make into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: sugarless cream cheese frosting
directions: In a bowl, whisk all ingredients together until smooth.

title: hot provolone squares
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and thyme; mix well.
Spread about 1 1/2 teaspoons cheese mixture on each bread slice.
Place slices on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 2 to 4 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: greek potato patties
directions: Mash the potatoes with butter and mix with beaten eggs and grated cheese.
Add the seasonings and blend thoroughly.
Form the potatoes into patties and dust with flour on all sides.
Fry in heated oil.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and eggs.
Add sugar and flour, then Karo syrup.
Add pecans which have been floured.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and
chill an hour.
Then roll into cheese ball and roll in
pecan
pieces.
Wrap
in wax paper or Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: rib marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Place racks of ribs in large Ziploc bag.
Pour marinade over ribs.
Seal bag.
Place in fridge at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill 30 to 35 minutes, basting often and turning.
Okay with pork or beef; unique sweet flavor.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Melt butter; add marshmallows.
Heat on stove at low; remove from heat when marshmallows are melted.
Add cornflakes; stir well.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown the ground beef in a frypan; drain off fat. Simmer sauce in a saucepan. Drain pasta after it is cooked. Put one layer of sauce and meat in 9 x 13 baking dish. Continue layering sauce, pasta and cheese. Save some cheese for topping. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbly.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops first, but not fully done.
Crumble bread; add onions, celery, salt, pepper and butter.
Mix well.
Lay pork chops on cookie sheet.
Put breaded mixture on top of pork chops. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot cheese salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and pineapple in a saucepan.
Bring to a simmer; set aside to cool.

title: buck's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add sausage and cook until red color disappears.
Add crumbled ground beef and cook until red disappears.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well and simmer slowly several hours, stirring periodically.
Let cool and refrigerate to allow grease to come to the top and remove.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
Mix grated cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Spread over mixed vegetables.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine and spread over mixture.
Cook at 350° until begins to bubble.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 1/2 stick oleo and cheese. Place in greased casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick oleo, melted.
Sprinkle over hot broccoli.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cracker snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Lay crackers side by side (one layer only).
In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in sugar. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Drizzle over entire surface of crackers. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack. Stores airtight for up to a week. Contains 46 calories each.

title: balsamic dressing
directions: Mix in blender. Slowly add oil in a slow stream; process until smooth. Cover and chill.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast and add remaining ingredients and then spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400 for 15-20 minutes. Adjust baking time if using a dark, non-stick pan. These make up nicely in the mini muffin tins also. Batter will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sesame seeds, sugar, broken noodles, and almonds.
Brown, stirring frequently.
Cool to room temperature. Wash and chop Bok Choy and onions with tops.
Make dressing of last 4 ingredients.
Combine them and shake in pint jar. Just before serving, toss greens, noodles mixture and dressing.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in water.
Beat into stiffly beaten egg whites until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until it stands in peaks. Drop on wax paper.

title: mexican fruit cake(no shortening)
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix with strawberries, egg yolks, water, gelatin and salad oil.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: easy maple nut bread
directions: Several hours before making bread, chop walnuts and add to maple syrup.
Let stand or soak overnight in refrigerator. Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, egg, milk and biscuit mix. Beat at high speed for 30 seconds.
Stir in nut mixture and pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Soak gelatine in cold water.
Heat milk until hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cool.
When cool, add 3 cups cream.
Melt butter and heat nuts until crisp.
Add 2 cups brown sugar.
Mix well into butter mixture.
Add nut mixture to ice cream when partly frozen.

title: chocolate pan cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa, shortening and water to a boil.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla. Bake in a greased oblong pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion into small pieces.
Add raisins and crumbled bacon.
Combine vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over broccoli and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain most of water, leave a little in bottom. Set carrots aside, add butter and brown sugar to water. Simmer for 2 minutes. Put carrots back in mixture. Coat them good. Let set for a while to absorb the flavor.

title: violet honey
directions: Stir violets into honey.
Place jar on a cloth in a pan of water (filled to neck of jar).
Bring to a
boil; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan; leave to cool.
Infuse for 7 days. Warm the honey, strain out violets and pour into a clean jar.
A lovely Victorian treat!

title: banana cake(sugar-free)
directions: Beat together mashed bananas and eggs until creamy.
Add flour and baking powder and beat well.
Stir in sliced bananas.
Pour mixture into an oiled and floured 8-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around a water chestnut; secure with a toothpick.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven until bacon is cooked.
Mix 1 cup ketchup and 1 cup sugar.
Put chestnuts wrapped in bacon after bacon is cooked in casserole dish; pour sugar and ketchup mixture over.
Warm in oven and serve as appetizers with a napkin while having a drink.
Delicious.

title: ginger cashew chicken
directions: Spray wok.
Stir-fry chicken.
Stir-fry onions, celery and garlic.
Add mushrooms, sprouts, snow peas, cashews, ginger, soy and chicken.
Heat until veggies are tender and chicken is done.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift together first five ingredients three times.
Add water. Fold in Miracle Whip and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in two 8-inch pans.
Does not take as long as other cakes.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Add all prepared ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: praline chewies
directions: Mix the melted butter and brown sugar; cool 15 minutes.
Add to the remaining ingredients; mix.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, lime juice and pineapple thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Thaw berries.
Place berries and their juice in blender; blend until smooth.
Add half of yogurt or ice cream; blend.
Turn off and scrape down the sides.
Add remaining yogurt or ice cream; blend.
Pour into glasses.
Yields 3 or 4 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by coffee spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Turn oven off.
Put cookies in oven and leave overnight.
Yields 60 to 70 cookies.

title: cheese straws
directions: With hands, mix butter and cheese.
Add in baking powder, salt, red pepper and 2 cups flour.
Slowly add in last cup of flour (may not use all) to consistency.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil corn syrup, water and sugar to 230°.
Add Spanish salted peanuts and continue boiling until reaches 300°.
Remove from stove and add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir and pour immediately on large, buttered cookie sheet.

title: spice potpourri
directions: Knead to form dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cutters.
Make a hole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crisp.
Cool.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Combine in blender.
Pour over one cut up chicken in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: soft shell crabs
directions: Rinse crabs under cold water and drain.
Coat them in mixture of bread crumbs, flour, salt and pepper.
Put 1/8 inch oil in a large frying pan, and fry them over medium heat, about 4 minutes on each side, until nicely browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over lowest heat.
The microwave works well at 50% power.
Add ice cream by small spoonfuls, beating with spoon after each addition.
Add nuts, if desired.
Remove from heat. Spoon in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 1/2 hours.
Keep in cool place.
When chilled, this fudge can be rolled into balls and rolled in ground nuts.
You may want to eliminate the nuts in the fudge then.

title: lemon delight
directions: Beat until it thickens; spread on cream cheese mixture. Spread on remaining Cool Whip.
Add finely chopped nuts over top for garnish.

title: amanda's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated. Will keep for 1 month.
Can be used for grilling out, as a dip, to marinate meat, as a Sloppy Joes mixture, etc.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown ribs.
Putting salt and pepper on the spareribs before browning them is optional.
Mix all ten of the remaining ingredients together.
Place spareribs in this mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: minted peas and onions
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onions in the butter, covered, over moderately low heat, stirring until they are softened.
Add the peas, mint and salt and pepper to taste and cook the mixture, stirring occasionally, until the peas are heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower in small amount of salted water for 15-20 minutes.
Drain well.
Prepare stuffing according to package. Break up cauliflower and place in greased baking dish.
Cover with stuffing and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-pepper spread
directions: Combine ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
Use as needed. Excellent on potatoes, steak, bread, crackers or for seasoning vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a jelly roll pan for 15 minutes; cool.
Cream together cream cheese, pudding and milk and spread over cake.
Sprinkle pineapple over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with shredded coconut, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate and serve cold.
Better made day before serving.
Serves 15 to 20 large portions.

title: eggplant regina
directions: Lightly brown eggplant in hot oil.
Place in layers in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Add layers of sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle tomatoes with a little marjoram and onion powder.
Add grated cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry and apple casserole
directions: Toss first 3 ingredients and put in casserole dish. Pour water over the fruit.
Mix topping and pour over fruit and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple butter
directions: Place apples in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 12 hours, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir and cook for 12 more hours on low.
Place in hot canning jars and seal.

title: fruit salsa
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Can be prepared 1 day ahead.

title: cucumber buttermilk dressing
directions: Press chopped cucumber between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Combine cucumber and remaining ingredients in small mixing bowl, stirring until well blended. Cover and chill dressing thoroughly. Serve dressing with salad greens.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: hot tomato soup
directions: In 3 quart saucepan combine all except sherry.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry.
Serve hot in cups or soup bowls.

title: peach parfait
directions: Crust:
Place rolled oats and almonds in 9-inch square, glass pan and toast at 350° for 5 minutes.
Add brown sugar and melted butter, then toast again for 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
(Save 1/2 cup crumbs for top.)

title: fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples, sugar and butter on stove in a saucepan.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Roll out can biscuits and add a teaspoon to each biscuit.
Fold over and fry in a skillet of hot oil.
Just like grandma made.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Very good.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix orange juice with milk.
Beat in pudding mix on low for 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients together.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, add buttermilk.
Dip chicken pieces or chicken breasts into buttermilk and then into batter.
Place into foil lined pan (13 x 9-inch).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, uncover and pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, an additional 15 minutes at 425°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg, flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Put on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Go through crab meat and check for shells.
Break bread into small pieces; moisten with milk.
Mix ingredients; shape into cakes.
Refrigerate and let set up.
Fry quickly until brown. Makes 4 to 6 cakes.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with all ingredients except marshmallows and cinnamon.
Place sweet potatoes in a casserole dish and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with marshmallows, sprinkle with cinnamon and bake 15 minutes more before taking out of oven.

title: texas brag cake
directions: Pour cherries into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar over cherries.
Pour or spoon pineapple over cherries and sugar.
Add the cake mix over all.
Cut oleo and spread over cake mix, then spread or sprinkle coconut over oleo.
Sprinkle pecans over all. Cover with foil lightly; bake at 325° until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into greased casserole dish.

title: asparagus crescent rolls
directions: Do not dilute Cheddar cheese soup.
Roll one stick of asparagus in 1 triangle roll.
Bake until brown.
Warm soup and pour over asparagus rolls.
Serve.

title: creamy cheese potato bake
directions: Thaw potatoes about 20 minutes.
Mix with other ingredients and top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes.

title: it's an old southern custom spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and margarine.
Stir in boiling water. Beat well.
Add milk, eggs and baking powder.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, pepper, sugar, salt, Tabasco sauce and garlic.
Set aside.
Cook tortellini following package directions until al dente, about 15 minutes.
Drain. Spoon into large bowl.
Toss dressing with pasta. Cool to lukewarm. Fold in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate, covered, several hours or overnight.
Remove 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.
Toss lightly before serving.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients in rice cooker and cook for approximately 30 minutes, or place in a large casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place in large container first 5 ingredients in layers.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over top of layered vegetables. Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes until done.
Pour off water.
Peel and mash potatoes with potato masher. Add sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nutmeg, ginger, lemon extract and milk.
(Use your own recipe for pie crust.)
Pour mixture into 2 pie crusts.
Bake 60 minutes.
Cool before cutting. Use half ingredients for 1 pie.

title: meatballs
directions: Make meatballs.
Mix applesauce and cornflakes.
Let soak. Blend next 5 ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Sprinkle with onion.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Do not use light sour cream.
Thaw coconut and mix with sugar and sour cream.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle noodles over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast chicken breast
directions: Mix together the oil, vinegar and soy sauce.
Combine salt, pepper and rosemary.
Cut garlic in half.
Thinly slice the other 2 cloves.
Loosen skin of chicken breast; brush half of the vinegar mixture under the skin.
Pat half of spice mixture.
Slip thin slices of garlic under skin in various locations.
Rub skin and inside breast cavity with garlic halves.
Brush other half of liquid mixture on skin.
Put other half of spice mixture on skin. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: luchow's potato salad
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes; boil in jackets until tender.
Let cool only enough to peel and slice.
Heat water and dissolve bouillon cube.
Pour stock over warm potatoes; add onion and celery.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Served 4 to 5.

title: quick reiska
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse and crumbly.
Add buttermilk and stir until mixture clings together.
Knead for several minutes.
Roll into round loaf.
Flatten to fit on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick entire surface with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and tear into pieces.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Place chicken in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter and mix with 1 package of crushed crackers.
Mix well and sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: onion meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, onion soup mix, milk and egg. Press mixture firmly into ungreased loaf pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch, leaving space around all sides.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chinese oven fried pork chops
directions: Beat egg, soy sauce, sherry, ginger and garlic salt together in a pie plate. Sprinkle bread crumbs on wax paper. Dip each pork chop into egg mixture, then press into bread crumbs, coating evenly on both sides. Arrange in a single layer on baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 minutes more or until chops are tender and show no pink.

title: gary's chili
directions: Brown ground meat with onions; drain.
Break up into little bits.
Put all in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Beat in egg yolks, flour and milk.
Add juice of lemon and grated rind.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked crust until firm (30 to 40 minutes) at 350°.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gerry's chili
directions: Brown beef.
Saute onions, celery and peppers.
In large pot, combine tomato juice, hot sauce, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, salt, chili powder, tomatoes and catsup.
Add beef, onion and pepper mixture to pot.
Cook 3 hours, then add beans. Delicious.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients together with hands and make into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Keep over hot water while dipping balls.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper to set.

title: tina's cajun surprise
directions: In a large cooking pot, stir flour and oil together until thoroughly mixed together.
Keep stirring mixture until flour is cooked or until turns a light brown.
Mix green peppers, onion, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Pour water until vegetable is covered or until you have thickness you prefer.
Cook until vegetables are cooked thoroughly.
Add seasoning at this time.
Add shrimp and crab or any meat you prefer.
Shrimp cooks in seconds, when skin turns pink shrimp is done.
You can serve over rice or as a soup.

title: open-face sandwiches
directions: Place bread slices on cookie sheet covered in aluminum foil. Layer bread slice with a slice of cheese, tomato and bacon.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts and bread turns crispy.

title: sherried banana cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake in two 9-inch round cake pans according to package directions.
Remove from pans and cool as directed. Place unpeeled bananas on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until very soft.
Remove bananas from peel and place in container of electric blender. Add butter, sherry and sugar. Blend until smooth.
Cool slightly. Slice each cake horizontally.
Place one layer on plate; spread with 1/3 banana filling. Repeat with two more layers and remaining banana filling.
Top with remaining cake layer.
Frost top and sides of cake with Whipped Cream Frosting. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine the cake mix, just 6 tablespoons oleo and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add egg.
Mix until well blended.
Press into prepared pan.
Pour pie filling over crust and spread to cover crumbs.
To reserved crumbs, in a large bowl, add remaining 1/2 cup oats, 2 tablespoons oleo, nuts and brown sugar.
Beat until mixed. Sprinkle over cherry mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely. Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: super rich mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins.
Peel and mash.
Combine potatoes with "butter" and yogurt.
Mix in chives.
Keep all hot in double boiler.
Add salt and butter to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crushed crackers.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with all but 1 cup of crackers.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle chestnuts over this and top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: xtra good pie crust
directions: Mix together flour, Crisco and salt.
Mix egg, vinegar and ice water; pour over first ingredients, then blend.
Makes approximately 3 crusts that will keep in the refrigerator.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Pour fruit juices and cherries in punch bowl over cake of ice. Add sparkling grape juice.
Serve in tall, hollow stemmed glasses.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and beat together the eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add the dry mixture to the egg mixture and stir well.
If desired, add one cup chopped nuts. Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Yields 2 loaves.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Mix together shortening, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.

In seperate bowl mix salt and flour. Gradually, add flour to creamy mixture forming dough. Form dough into balls, then dip into egg whites, to coat. Roll balls in nuts to cover. Pleace on greased cookie sheet. Push your thumb in center of cookie ball. Fill with jelly. Bake for 10-12 min.

title: bessie mae's punch
directions: Fill all cans with water (34 ounces).
Put strawberries in last.
May float orange slices in bowl.
Very refreshing.

title: sausage breakfast
directions: Pat rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over sausage. Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cook onion and mushrooms over low heat until tender.
Add turkey, gravy and spaghetti.
If gravy seems thick, thin it with a little milk.
Heat mixture until it bubbles, stirring frequently.
Turn into a baking dish and top with the cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Serve with crisp celery sticks and carrot sticks.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crock-pot rabbit or squirrel
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.
Mix all ingredients and pour over meat. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.
Thicken liquid (after cooking) with either flour or cornstarch mixed with water.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder with soup. Butter the casserole dish and arrange broccoli in the bottom, then add chicken.
Pour soup over broccoli and chicken.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese, mixed with 1 cup bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Heat one cup of milk and the sugar until the sugar is free from lumps.
Mix the cornstarch, one-half cup of milk and egg yolks; add to the hot mixture slowly.
Cook in a double boiler until thick, stirring constantly, then for ten minutes longer.
Add butter. When cool, pour into a baked shell.
Cover with a meringue made from the stiffly beaten egg whites and powdered sugar.
Brown in the oven.

title: corn and bean bake
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix all together and put in 12 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1 stick melted oleo and 1/2 small box of Cheez-Its crackers, crushed and mixed together.
Put on top of corn and beans.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Mix 1 package of jello, 1 envelope Knox gelatine and 1 cup hot water.
When cool, pour slowly into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.
Mix 1 cup milk and 1 cup hot water.
Mix 2 envelopes of Knox gelatine and 1 cup of hot water.
Then mix the milk and Knox gelatine mixture together and cool.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat egg; add buttermilk and beat.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Add oil; mix.
Pour into round pancakes on hot, oiled frypan.
Serve with hot syrup.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a saucepan combine broth, onion, seasonings and broccoli. Boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender. Remove bay leaf.
Place 1/2 vegetable mixture in a blender or food processor.
Cover and blend 30 to 60 seconds until smooth.
Repeat with remaining vegetable mixture.
Set all aside.

title: croutons
directions: Spread bread slices with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Stack slices and cut into cubes.
Put on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 250° and bake for 30 to 60 minutes or until crisp.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pico de gallo(rooster's beak)
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, cucumbers, radishes, cilantro and chiles. Squeeze lime juice over vegetables.
Add salt to taste; stir. Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups.
This salsa enhances meats.

title: ruby's pineapple icing
directions: Cook until thick enough to spread on cake layers.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans, peas and pimento.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: black-eyed peas stew
directions: Rinse peas.
Cook in water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.
Serves 6.

title: thick tomato-vegetable-beef soup
directions: Cook macaroni in 1 cup water in saucepan until tender and water is evaporated, stirring frequently.
Add vegetable-beef soup and 1 soup can water; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice, tomato soup, remaining soup can water and salt; mix well.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cherry glaze
directions: Combine ingredients in	a
small saucepan.
Cook, stirring, over
medium heat
until
mixture
boils
and
thickens slightly. Brush over turkey during
last
15 to 20 minutes of baking or broiling or serve as a sauce.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: plum fun cake
directions: In 9-inch square pan, combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously with rubber spatula for 1 minute. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: ark play dough
directions: Boil water and salt; add food coloring and remove from heat. Add flour, alum and oil.
Stir well and knead.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Pile into graham cracker crust.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain.
Add soups, peppers and picante sauce.
Mix well.
Salt to taste.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make a layer of Doritos, then a layer of meat. Alternate until meat mixture is gone.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and meat is bubbly.

title: cracklins cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, margarine and butter for 2 minutes.
Lay graham crackers flat on baking sheet tightly packed.
Top with walnuts. Pour sugar syrup over all and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ginny cake
directions: Take fully baked and cooled chocolate cake and spread chocolate pudding over entire cake.
Top with Cool Whip and shaved Hershey bar.

title: italian chicken
