directions: Melt butter; add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce to butter.
Dip chicken in butter sauce.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle leftovers on top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan or 2-8 inch round pans.
Bake 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Top chicken with cheese.
Combine soup and broth.
Spoon over chicken and sprinkle stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: mom's chicken
directions: Combine dressing, marmalade and soup mix.
Pour over chicken in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This recipe is easy and quick.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: removal of plastic container odors
directions: Crumble up old newspaper.
Place into the closed container. Leave paper in the closed container for several days, or as long as it takes for the odor to be gone.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and fruit cocktail, including juice, together. Add flour, salt and soda.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix coconut and brown sugar together.
Sprinkle over top of cake. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese-pineapple boats
directions: Select a pineapple with fresh green leaves, cutting pineapple lengthwise into quarters through green top.
Cut along curved edges of quarters with grapefruit knife to remove fruit.
Cut off pineapple core; cut fruit into chunks.
Drain fruit and invert shell to drain.
Place pineapple chunks, halved strawberries and melon balls in large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon ginger and the lime juice; toss.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Stir in cheese; spoon mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with almonds and ginger.
Spoon yogurt onto each serving and garnish with whole strawberries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: okie's banana pudding
directions: Separate eggs, beat egg yolks, then add sugar and milk.
(If you use evaporated milk, dilute with water.)
Cook this mixture until it boils.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup tomato soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg thoroughly.
In baking pan, shape firmly into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat loaf is done.
In small saucepan, mix 2 tablespoons drippings, remaining tomato soup and water.
Heat through.
Serve with meat loaf.

title: garden vegetable twist
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, in 1 tablespoon hot olive oil, cook broccoli and carrots with basil and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese; add macaroni and chicken.
Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings. 350 calories, 11 g fat.

title: muffins
directions: Mix
first
ingredients;
add remaining ingredients. Mix and fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry crunch coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for topping.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until very light and thick. Gradually add granulated sugar.
Beat well after each addition. Stir in melted, but not hot, butter.
Add mixture of flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: barbecue hamburger casserole
directions: Heat water on high in large, deep frying pan on top of stove. Once it boils, add soup mix; stir and add meat.
Brown meat; do not drain.
Turn stove down to medium heat and add baked beans and barbecue sauce.
Cover, stirring, until done, approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in flour to thicken.
Serve, open-face sandwich style over bread or onion roll.

title: jello punch
directions: Heat sugar for syrup and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into gallon jugs and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa.
Blend in vanilla, vinegar, oil and water.
Pour batter into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix the flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over margarine.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli, onion, celery, water, bouillon, pepper and garlic powder in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer mixture to blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Return mixture to casserole.
Mix together cream and flour until smooth. Stir into broccoli mixture and microwave on High, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Stir in lemon juice and Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Mix together first four ingredients.
Combine with mayonnaise mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Note:
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.

title: savory squash
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients to squash and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: puppy mix
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Put in a shallow pan.
Put puppy's faces into
the mix.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack firmly into an ungreased
(8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: spaghetti
directions: Spray a large skillet with Pam cooking spray.
In a separate pot, start water boiling for noodles.
Once water comes to a boil, add noodles and allow to boil until noodles are limp.
Drain water and add butter to noodles.
Put meat in skillet and season with Italian seasoning, parsley flakes, Tony Chachere's (a pinch of each).
Brown and drain meat.
Place meat back in skillet; add McCormick spaghetti seasoning, Hunt's spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and Ro-Tel.
Heat for a few minutes on a medium temperature while stirring.
Serve sauce over noodles.
Goes well with salad, garlic bread and iced tea.

title: diabetic pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in pan with all ingredients on medium heat. Stir as cucumbers heat.
Bring to a boil.
Have jars and lids hot. Place in jars and seal.

title: cranberry pot roast
directions: Brown meat in own fat (trimmed from meat) or in cooking fat, if needed, in large frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over meat.
Add cloves and cinnamon.

title: spiced peach tea
directions: Mix all and store in container.
Serve hot or cold.

title: calorie-counter's coleslaw
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cabbage, carrot and onion. Set aside.

title: salsa chicken
directions: In skillet, saute chicken in hot oil over medium heat, about 10 minutes or until browned evenly.

title: blowing bubble mix
directions: Mix dishwashing liquid, sugar and water.
Stir slowly until thoroughly mixed.
Let mixture stand for 24 hours.
Place mixture in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
This will make your bubbles last longer.
Now enjoy!

title: shrimp pate
directions: In a food processor fitted with metal blade, combine mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended. Shape into a ball or spoon into a crock.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight for flavors to blend.
May be refrigerated for up to 2 days.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with crackers or bread rounds.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: deviled meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground beef, bread crumbs, green pepper, 1/2 can tomato sauce, egg and salt.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste several times.

title: broiled basil eggplant
directions: Whisk 1/4 cup olive oil and next 4 ingredients.
Brush the 3 tablespoons olive oil on both sides of eggplant.
Salt and pepper. Broil until tender and light brown, turning once.
Place overlapping on ovenproof platter.
Top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Whisk olive oil and lemon juice mixture again and spoon over garnish with fresh basil and serve immediately.

title: tomato bisque in a blender
directions: Puree all ingredients but avocado in blender or food processor. Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Gently pour over avocado cubes, with low-fat tortilla chips.
Serves 4.

title: "impossible" coconut pie
directions: Beat all together until light in color; fold in coconut.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Pie makes own crust.
Makes 2 small or 1 large pie.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Clean, devein and peel butterfly shrimp.
Place them in pan; mix butter, shallots, garlic, lemon juice, parsley, bread crumbs, egg yolk, hot sauce, salt and pepper in bowl.
Spoon over raw shrimp; place under broiler for 3 to 5 minutes, check not to overcook shrimp.
Spoon leftover sauce over shrimp and serve over linguine or rice.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburg.
When half browned, add salt, garlic, mushrooms and oregano.
Finish browning and pour off the fat.
Add diced olives and soup and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put split buns on a baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven until browned lightly (about 5 minutes).
Top buns with hamburg mixture and sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve open-faced.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw 1 loaf of bread slightly and break in small pieces. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let other loaf thaw; set aside. In a pan, melt margarine. Add cinnamon, milk, sugar, nuts and pudding.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool slightly and pour over rolls.
Break the other loaf of bread in small pieces over first layer.
Let rise in warm place to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately on large platter.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Place butter and cream cheese in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes or until soft.
Beat.
Add 1 box confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and mix well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar; beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to oil mixture.
Add vanilla extract, apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat the eggs.
Stir in the milk.
Sift and add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the fat or cooking oil.
Cut up the fruit or vegetables.
Add to or dip in fritter batter from blender. Drop into hot deep fat fryer at 375° until brown.
Drain and serve with syrup, gravy or powdered sugar.

title: orange nut bars
directions: Combine undiluted orange juice concentrate, rolled oats, fruit and nuts.
Reserve.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs, mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir into molasses mixture.
Blend well.
Turn into greased 24 x 14 x 2-inch pan or two 18 x 9-inch pans.
Spread evenly.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Frost with Orange Icing when cool.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Decorate with candied cherries.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/3 cup cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep dish peach cobbler
directions: Dump entire contents of peaches in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer evenly with cake mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Poke cake mix with wooden spoon handle throughout.
Do not mix together!

title: feel good cheesecake
directions: Prepare an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Make fine crumbs with graham crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Combine boiling water, lemon rind, lemon juice and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Chill until it is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Put 2 tablespoons water, cottage cheese and lemon extract into blender.
Cover and turn to high speed for 10 to 15 seconds.
Add gelatin mixture; turn to high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers over the top.
Slice strawberries and arrange on top.
Chill.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour milk in saucepan and let simmer.
In a bowl mix egg yolks, sugar and flour, then pour the mixture into milk and let thicken. Pour pecans into the pan.
After the filling gets thick, put in the butter and vanilla.
Then put into baked pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: reduced calorie strawberry angel pie
directions: Pour water over berries, let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain water from berries, into pan, reserving berries. Sprinkle gelatin over 2 tablespoons liquid drained from berries. Whisk cornstarch and egg yolk into remaining water.
Cook over medium heat until mix boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin, sweetener and extracts stirring until gelatin and sweetener dissolve.
Stir in berries; chill 1/2 hour or until mix is partially set.
Beat egg whites, skim milk powder, ice water in chilled bowl.
Fold into berry mix.
Spoon into crust; chill until set.
Makes 6 servings, 156 calories each.

title: great-grandma bowden's salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and vinegar.
Heat on medium and then add milk.
Cook until it thickens.

title: the willows' blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in covered jar in refrigerator until used.

title: brazos river steamboat pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs, corn syrup, vanilla, margarine and salt.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream or Cool Whip.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Makes 4 layers.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together; add a bottle of 7-Up to taste.

title: hummus-i
directions: Blend beans, tahini, lemon juice, salt, garlic and water. Mix in 2 Tbsp. olive oil by hand.
Arrange in dish.
Pour remaining olive oil and garnish with olives, snipped parsley, and paprika.

title: german potato bake
directions: Prepare instant potatoes according to package directions, omitting butter.
Add cream cheese; beat well.
Stir in 1 beaten egg, onion and parsley.
Blend thoroughly.
Transfer to a well-greased 1-quart baking dish or souffle dish.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender, drain thoroughly.
Combine potatoes, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with mixer until blended.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Pile lightly into a buttered 2 quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight if you wish.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased and floured bundt pan and bake at 325 degrees for 55-60 minutes.

title: sweet may dressing
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, mustard and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add whipped cream before serving.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Prepare shortening and flour in frying pan as for gravy.
Add onion, peppers, allspice, black pepper, sugar and vinegar (vinegar can be substituted with juice from sweet pickles which gives a good flavor).
Into this mixture, pour tomatoes and let simmer (not boil) for 30 minutes.
This is good with vegetables or meats.

title: herb-roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove fat, neck, liver and gizzard from cavity of chicken.
Rinse and drain.
Rub chicken inside and out with garlic.
Stuff with herbs.
Add onion, if not using chives.
Save some herbs for outside of chicken.
Spray or grease rack of broiler pan.
Place chicken breast-side down.
Press down to flatten.
Put in oven and immediately lower temperature to 375°.
Roast 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until skin is crisp and legs easily move up and down.
Remove from oven and let sit for 5 to 10 minutes before carving.
If herbs are not available, carrot and a piece of celery may also be put in cavity.

title: grandma's ice cream
directions: Whip egg yolks with sugar.
Add vanilla. Whip Milnot.
Whip egg whites and add to mixture.
Add milk.

title: hot texas cocoa cake
directions: Combine in a saucepan and bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa, cooking oil and water.
Stir in the flour, sifted with the sugar. Add and mix well the remainder of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Top with frosting.

title: chicken in italian sauce
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, place chicken with meat pieces around edges.
Stir together sauce mix and liquids.
Pour over top.
Cover and microwave on High 16 to 18 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Stir tomatoes and mushrooms into chicken.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Do not salt.
When cool, tear chicken into pieces.
Melt butter and stir in stuffing mix.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put layer of stuffing mix on bottom.
Add layer of chicken, one can of cream of chicken soup and pour one can of chicken broth.
Repeat layers.
Save some stuffing for top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning until well blended.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with picante sauce and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork butt pie
directions: Cook meat with onion, salt, pepper, 1/2 of cinnamon and cloves; add 1 cup water.
Keep stirring until it boils.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat; drain fat.
Then add remaining cloves and cinnamon.
Mash potato (do not add milk or butter).
Add meat with potatoes; mix well.
Place in pie shell and top on it.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: super stew easy
directions: Prepare the vegetables and place in large Dutch oven or casserole dish.
Mix soup, water, wine and any seasonings you like.
Cover and bake in oven for 3 hours at 350°.
Serve with tossed salad and warm sourdough bread.

title: junk rice
directions: Fry onion, mushrooms and minute steaks.
Flavor with garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; drain.
Cook rice according to package directions and add to other ingredients.
If you prefer rice slightly more spicy, replace beef flavored rice with Spanish flavored rice.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Mix next 3 together and add all at once.
Stir only until mixed; batter will have lumps.

title: seven-can king ranch casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In a large bowl, soak the tortillas in the broth for 2 minutes.
Remove tortillas to a plate and set aside. Add the two soups, tomatoes and green chilies to the broth. Mix well.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/3 of the tortillas, 1/3 of the sauce, 1/3 of the cheese and 1/2 of the chicken.
Repeat twice, ending with tortillas, sauce and cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: huckleberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk. Mix well and pour over melted margarine.
DO NOT STIR.
Combine 1 cup sugar and berries in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over batter.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Pare and slice eggplant; cook until tender in vinegar and boiling water to cover.
Drain eggplant, mash and beat in remaining ingredients.
Drop batter from spoon into hot deep fat. Fry until golden.
Yields about 10 fritters.

title: cucumbers in turmeric
directions: Peel the cucumbers.
Cut into quarters lengthwise.
Scrape away seeds and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix with 2 tablespoons salt.
Refrigerate for an hour.
Wash the cucumbers in fresh water three times and drain well.
Press in a clean dish towel to remove as much moisture as possible.
Saute the onion, garlic and ginger root in the peanut oil until the onion is soft.
Add the turmeric, remaining tablespoon of salt and sugar.
Stir well.
Add the vinegar and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour mixture over the cucumbers in a glass or crockery bowl.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Stir a few times.
These are great with lamb dishes and curries.
They will keep (covered) in the refrigerator for a few weeks.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt margarine, then all milk and vanilla.
Add cocoa.
Stir good.
Add a little sugar at a time until all added.
Stir good and add pecans.
Pour in greased pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour into a bowl and chill.
Blend strawberry or grape preserves into chilled pudding.
Gently fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill until ready to serve.
If desired, garnish with whipped cream and a whole maraschino cherry.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge beef in flour.
In a heavy skillet, melt butter with oil and brown the beef.
Slowly add bouillon to beef, stirring well. Bring to a boil.
Combine sour cream mixture into beef mixture. Turn heat to low and bring to a bare simmer.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently and never allowing mixture to boil. Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 21 g, fat 36 g, calories 427.

title: red hot jello
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Dissolve jello in water and stir in applesauce.
Let set before serving.

title: amalgamation cake(the grace eidson family's favorite)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Cook in layer cake pan until done.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour into well-greased and floured large muffin pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and prick several times with a fork. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half, lengthwise, and scoop out pulp, leaving 1/8-inch thick shells.
(Reserve pulp for other uses.)
Cut each potato shell lengthwise into 4 strips and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Spray potato strips lightly with cooking spray.
Combine salt, paprika and pepper.
Sprinkle over potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 14 minutes or until crisp.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients. Add the next 10 ingredients and mix well. Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour. Add cheese and tortillas; simmer 20 more minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crushed crackers and margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine instant pudding, milk and ice cream; pour over crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top; sprinkle with chopped Heath bars.

title: no bake stack cake
directions: Spread apple butter on graham crackers and layer. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: salmon puffs
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, milk and soup mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; let set 5 minutes before serving. Tuna can be used as an alternate or double recipe using salmon and tuna for a tasty flavor.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and blend.
Put into a quart container and use as needed.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish.
Add strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash and peel firm-ripe figs.
Add sugar and lemon juice to 8 cups boiling water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add figs.
Boil until clear.
Add lemons when figs are about 2/3 done.
If the syrup becomes too thick before figs are clear, add boiling water, 1/2 cup at a time.
Let stand 12 to 24 hours in a cool place. Pack preserves in hot jars.
Process pints and quarts 30 minutes at simmering (180° to 185°) in a water bath canner.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix as directed on package using only 1/3 cup milk.
Put in black iron pot (greased).
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until browned.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until tested done. Cool.
Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.
I use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: french rice
directions: Combine soup and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a
greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: prosciutto roll-ups
directions: On floured surface, roll out half the pastry to 12 x 10-inch rectangle. Spread with half the mustard, leaving 1/4-inch border. Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and arrange half the meat over top. Brush border with water. Starting at short end, roll up jelly roll style to center and turn over.
Using serrated knife, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on parchment paper lined baking sheet and press lightly. Repeat with other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or up to 1 day. Brush egg over roll-ups. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes until puffy and golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place the eggs in a saucepan.
Cover with cold water.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain off hot water.
Let eggs stand in cold water a few minutes, then peel and cut them lengthwise in half.
Scoop out the yolks and mash them in a bowl. Add mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Spoon the mixture back into the hollows of the egg whites.
Sprinkle paprika on top of each egg half.

title: chicken and broccoli and rice
directions: In an 11 x 13-inch pan, place chicken pieces.
Add rice to cover evenly.
In separate bowl, mix broccoli and cheese sauce, milk, water and butter until well blended.
Pour mixture over chicken and rice.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and combine with dressing and chill.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: In a large stockpot, saute the bacon, onion and garlic in butter and oil until the onion becomes soft (8 to 10 minutes).
Add the carrots, celery and potatoes and saute for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add the tomatoes.
Dissolve the 2 bouillon cubes in 2 cups water and pour into the soup.
Then add corn, zucchini, bay leaves, thyme, basil and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Turn after 7 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and roll into balls. Chill. Melt 1 package semi-sweet chocolate and 1/2 block paraffin in double boiler. Dip chilled balls in hot chocolate. Cool on waxed paper.

title: broccoli meat loaf roll
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, bread, catsup, milk, salt, pepper, onion and green peppers.
Pat hamburger mixture on a piece of aluminum foil 18 x 15-inches.
Put broccoli to within 1/2 inch of top of hamburger mix.
Put ham on top of hamburger mix.
Put ham on top of broccoli roll, beginning at small end of aluminum foil.
Press edges and ends to seal roll.
Place in a shallow pan, cook, uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the soda.
Pour over popcorn in a large bowl; stir well!
Bake at 250° for 1 hour in roasters.
Break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: weepless pie meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar; stir in water. Cook over low heat until thickened and clear, stirring constantly. Cool. Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar well after each addition. Beat until very creamy. Pile on pie and bake 30 minutes at 325°, until golden brown. Covers 8 or 9-inch pie.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Roll in walnut size balls.
Roll in mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
(They will puff up and then flatten down.)

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in boiler.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup of peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Drop on nonstick cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Cool.

title: lydia's rice pudding
directions: Cook water, rice and salt for 7 minutes per instructions with raw rice.
Add butter and milk and cook on low for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Wash cabbage and chop fine.
Chop onion.
Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Put half of cabbage in deep baking dish and cover with ground beef and onion.
Do not add grease.
Put remainder of cabbage on top.
Pour undiluted tomato soup over mixture.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 325°.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and add 1 tablespoon creme de menthe.
Bake according to directions; cool.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken with salt and shred. Preheat oven at 350°. Combine soups, broth, and Ro-Tel. Mix. Alternate layers of chicken, onion, tortillas, sauce, and cheese in a greased 9 x 13 inch casserole dish. Repeat layering, ending with cheese. Bake 35 minutes. Good with sour cream and salsa.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a loaf pan.
Bake for approximately 50 minutes, until done.
After 45 minutes, watch venison meat loaf so it doesn't burn the top of meat loaf.
Spoon part of the fat off; save.
Pour over slices of venison meat loaf. Any leftovers go great with scrambled eggs.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown onion and hamburger meat.
Add drained corn and beans. Simmer about 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread.

title: quick and easy peach pie
directions: Pour all but 1/2 cup peach juice in pie shell.
Make a mixture of the juice, egg, sugar, butter or oleo and flour.
Pour over peaches in pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if you like.
Bake in 300° oven until brown on top.

title: promise branberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl soak cereal in milk for 5 minutes.
Stir in Promise, honey, berries, egg whites and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
With a rubber spatula, fold flour mixture into berry bran mixture, just enough to moisten.
Do not overmix. Evenly distribute among muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour 1 cup broth over chicken. Mix all ingredients and place over chicken.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: cho-caramel squares
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk in double boiler or microwave. Set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and flour.
In large bowl combine dry cake mix, oleo and 1/3 cup milk.
Press 1/2 of dough in pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake.
Spread caramel over chips.
Crumble remaining dough on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Then put in refrigerator before serving.
Cut into tiny squares.

title: boiled fish or prawns
directions: Boil stock or water.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Let boil until tomatoes are cooked.
Add radish and let simmer for a few minutes. Add prawns or fish and simmer.
After a few minutes, add salt to taste, then add spinach or mustard greens and simmer until done.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Add flour; stir well.
Add sugar, corn, tomatoes, soup and water. Simmer 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup batter onto heated griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn and cook until golden; serve with syrup or honey.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Bake at 350° for about 4 hours, or until the popcorn blows the ass off the turkey.

title: frozen angel salad
directions: Note:
Can use 2 packages of Dream Whip instead of cream and sugar.
Makes 28 or 29.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and salt in water approximately 15 minutes. Drain.
Put half of macaroni in casserole dish.
Slice half of cheese on top of macaroni.
Pour in half of sweetened tomatoes. Repeat with other half of each.
Put several slices of butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 400° approximately 50 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and toss well.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a separate bowl, mixing well.
Pour dressing over crab mixture and toss lightly.
When ready to serve, place crab mixture on a bed of lettuce and sprinkle with noodles and almonds. Serves 6 to 12.

title: butternut squash
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs, mix well and spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put all ingredients in large bowl (ground beef, tomato sauce, diced onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, egg, bread and seasonings).
Mix thoroughly.
Put into baking dish and cover top of meat loaf with thin layer of ketchup. Cover with foil.
Bake for about 1 hour or until done clear through.
Serves 5 people.

title: dish pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a very large bowl, cream sugars, oil and eggs.

title: sawmill biscuits
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into biscuits with cutter.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 biscuits.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and dates.
Bring to a boil for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off eye and add the vanilla, then stir in mixed Rice Krispies and pecans.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.
When warm, roll in balls and drop in confectioners sugar to coat.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Combine liquids and pour over dry ingredients.
Stir just until blended and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked ham with mustard sauce
directions: Remove ham from can and wash off.
Place in pan with 1-inch of water and bake in 250° to 300° oven for about 3 hours.
Remove from oven and pour water off.
Pour on mustard sauce and bake another hour at 200°.

title: festive broccoli casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine celery, onion, green pepper and butter.
Microwave 3 minutes at High.
Add broccoli and microwave 5 minutes at High, stirring once during cooking.
Add rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Microwave 8 minutes at High.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese.
Microwave 1 minute at High or until cheese melts.

title: billy's saturday morning pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and bake on a 400° griddle.
Makes about 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: arroz amarillo con choros y camarones(yellow rice, mussel and shrimp casserole)
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Saute onion and pepper until transparent.
Add garlic, parsley, tomato, bay leaf, nutmeg and thyme.
Mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat until mushy (about 15 minutes).
Add the shrimp to the saute and cook until it turns pink.
Combine wine with hot water, lemon juice (bottled is fine), salt and hot sauce.
Pour into pot.
Stir to mix and cook, covered, 10 minutes more.
Now add the rice and the 2 1/2 cups of water, the mussels and peas.
Bring to a quick boil; stir and distribute ingredients well in a 3-quart casserole with lid.
Place in preheated 325° oven for only 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Uncover and garnish with pimiento strips and parsley.
Pour beer over all.
Cover again and allow to stand 15 minutes longer, before serving.
Yields 6 generous servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding together with 3 cups of the liquid from the fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: fast fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to
375°.	Place
fruit in bottom of well-greased deep dish.	Mix 1/2
cup
sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk;
pour
evenly over fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top of batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.

title: chinese shrimp toast
directions: Remove crust from bread; cut each bread slice into 4 triangles. Set aside until shrimp mixture is complete.
Chop shrimp, water chestnuts and bacon fat very finely.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate mixture until firm.
Heat oil in wok or deep skillet.
Spread shrimp mixture on each bread triangle, covering edges.
Place in hot oil, shrimp side down, first.
Cook until shrimp mixture is light brown (does not take very long so keep an eye on it).
Flip sides and immediately remove from oil. Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: In large bowl, blend all ingredients at low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Let rise.
Divide; roll in circles.
Butter and cut in pie wedge; roll up.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise. Bake at 375°.
Makes about 20.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix together bread crumbs/cubes, onion, oleo, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each pork chop. Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute onion and bell pepper in stick of butter.
Cook one package of vermicelli in chicken broth.
Do not drain!
Add chicken, onion, bell pepper and butter mixture, cream of mushroom soup and Velveeta cheese, cut into small cubes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir occasionally.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook until thick. Remove from fire and add orange jello; let cool and add bananas and nuts.
Put in plain or vanilla wafer pie crust.
Top with whipped cream or small Cool Whip.
You can add a few chopped pecans on top of whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: horseradish pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in cold water. Pack in jars with a stick of horseradish in the center.
After the sugar, salt and vinegar have been brought to a boil, pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: my own chili
directions: Crumble raw meat into large pan.
Add juice, Chili-O, chili powder, pepper, sugar and kidney beans.
Simmer until meat is done.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and stir until foaming stops. Add 1/2 cup dry cracked wheat.
Simmer.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Put all of the yogurt in a bowl.
Stir in all of the Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into crust.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Eat when ready!

title: cincinnati chili
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, green pepper, onions, garlic and chili powder until beef is browned and vegetables are tender. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, kidney beans, vinegar and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Can be served over cooked spaghetti or cooked rice.
Garnish with cheese.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Dice zucchini and cook until soft, then drain.
Mash cooked zucchini; drain off excess liquid.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook milk, sugar, butter and cocoa in saucepan for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting time when it reaches a full rolling boil. Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter. Stir well and place by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: a different kind of chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients. Add next 4 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: luscious chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate	bar,
milk and marshmallows.
Let cool. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill.

title: stromboli
directions: Defrost bread dough. With roller, stretch out dough into a rectangle as long as a cookie sheet and about as wide. (A pinch of flour on dough will help.) After dough is stretched, combine 1 egg yolk (be sure to keep the white), minced garlic, Parmesan cheese and oregano in small bowl; mix until all ingredients are covered in yolk. Spread mixture on half of bread dough. Add toppings. Fold bread dough lengthwise. Be sure to pinch ends tightly. Lightly paint egg whites on top of dough. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, syrup, milk, salt and vanilla.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Pour into three 9-inch unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Bring pineapple and apple juice to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Whip in yogurt. Chill.
Serve over fruit or plain cake.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Heat 2 cups of water; add jello and sugar.
Next add juices (cold), then remaining water, sherbet and ginger ale.

title: orange spice rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons cracker crumb mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe ring mold; set mold and remaining crumb mixture aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; cut in 1/4 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add orange juice and milk, stirring with a fork just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 8 or 10 times.

title: no bake cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon while hot, then cool. Cook sugar, flour, cornstarch, salt and milk until thick.
Add chunk oleo and vanilla.
Cool slightly and pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: croquettes
directions: Make plain mashed potatoes.
Fry ground beef and chopped onion.
Mix them up and add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Make the shape like a column or whatever you like.
Coat them with all-purpose flour.
Dip into blended eggs with a little water. Coat with bread crumbs.
Deep fry them.
Serve them with tonkatsu sauce (or mixed ketchup and Worcestershire sauce).
Also, you can arrange the ingredients and make it vegetarian or whatever you like.

title: date coconut puffs
directions: Bring dates, butter, egg and sugar to a boil.
Remove from burner and stir until cool.
Butter hands and roll into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. In small bowl, mix cornmeal with buttermilk; set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, baking powder, baking soda, egg, 1/4 cup salad oil and the cornmeal mixture; stir until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan; bake 30 minutes.
Makes 12 squares.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook zucchini and butter for 10 minutes, then add parsley, pepper, basil, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Add this spice mixture to zucchini.
Beat eggs and then add cheese.
Combine all and place in pie shell;
bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let set 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt Crisco. Add eggs and sugar and beat well. Sift cocoa and flour together, add to mixture of eggs and sugar. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: linda's chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Drain and cut up.
Mix with soups, milk and margarine.
Heat to boiling.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add noodles, mix together.

title: shrimp au gratin
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables.
Stir in flour; cook, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks and thoroughly combine with half and half.
Gradually add egg and milk mixture to flour and sauteed vegetables to make a white sauce.
Add enhancer and next 3 seasonings.
After sauce is thickened, then add wine and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Fill individual serving dishes and top with grated, shredded cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is bubbling.

title: easy vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Mix all ingredients well; let stand overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: hot tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, celery slices, green peppers, pimento and almonds. In separate bowl, combine mayo, lemon juice, onion, celery seed and salt. Blend mixture together, tossing lightly. Place in 8- inch greased baking dish. Top with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350 degree for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated.

title: cheezy chowder
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until tender, then add milk and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer until hot.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool completely.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pat down graham crackers, then one at a time layer rest of ingredients.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over ingredients in the baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: western baked beans and sausage(preparation time: 1 hour)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon strips. Stir well. Top with bacon strips.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Enjoy!

title: barbecue
directions: Buy roasts of same size or close.
Cook them either together or separately in oven or crock-pots, until "fall apart tender".
Cool. Take roasts and remove bones, fat, etc. and save broth of both, but keep meat and broth separate.
Put all meat, chopped onion, bottle of ketchup, 1 cup brown sugar and some liquid smoke (1 tablespoon). Heat thoroughly.
Add more sugar and some broth if necessary.
Use remaining broth for soup or noodles.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Mix cinnamon with flour in small bowl.
Add whole eggs to sugar and oil mixture.
Add flour and oil mixture, then mix in carrots and walnuts, then vanilla and black walnut flavoring.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: austrian ravioli
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender, about 7 minutes.
Drain and mix with tomatoes and tomato sauce in large bowl.
Saute garlic clove in olive oil over medium heat until it begins to brown.
Remove clove from oil and cook meat, stirring to keep loose.
Add meat to macaroni mixture.
Stir in peas and grated cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pan.
Chill.
Cut in squares.
One level tablespoon is same as 1 package.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until pudding is dissolved.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Add marshmallows; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: "great" cake
directions: First Layer: In 13 x 9 pan, bake cake mix according to directions. Cool.

title: baked rice
directions: *One tablespoon butter or margarine combined with 1 tablespoon olive oil is good, also.

title: easy butterscotch sauce
directions: Simmer sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Makes one cup.
Serve over ice cream.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: In saucepan melt oleo; add to this the Cheez Whiz and mix thoroughly.
Put in casserole the broccoli and rice.
Pour cheese mixture over this and combine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 7 minutes.
This recipe doubles nicely.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix all ingredients together in a covered dish and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, drain juices off and mix in 1/4 cup salad oil if desired.

title: dot's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, refrigerate and serve.

title: honey wings
directions: Cut the wings in three pieces.
Wash thoroughly.
Using the 2 larger portions, season with seasoning salt.
Batter with flour and deep fry.
Slightly drain, dip cooked wing portions in honey until covered.
Lay in baking dish, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spicy chicken salad
directions: Poach chicken breasts.
Cool in poaching liquid.
Remove meat from bones and cut into 1/4-inch dice.
Add celery, grapes, onion, apple, almonds, salt and pepper to chicken and toss.

title: strada
directions: Butter 9 x 13 pan lightly.

Cut crust from bread and put half of bread on bottom of pan edge to edge. Use more bread if needed. Mix ham and cheese and spread over top of bread on bottom of pan. Put rest of bread on top of ham and cheese. Mix eggs, salt, milk and mustard and pour slowly over to saturate bread. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: round roast in casserole
directions: Make a marinade of wine, olive oil, garlic, red pepper, remaining seasonings and salt.
Place roast in it and marinate for at least 24 hours.
Remove roast; strain marinade and set aside. Dry meat, then massage it with sugar and brown in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place in Dutch oven and fill with beef broth to 1/2 the depth of roast.
Lay marrow bones beside it and cover pan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Slice carrot, mushrooms and onions.
Add to meat and cook an hour longer, still covered.
Add strained marinade and cook another hour without the cover.
Saute chopped shallot in butter.
Brown flour in a dry pan and stir shallots into it.
Add 1 cup of sauce from meat and blend well, then combine with juices from casserole, removing the marrow bones first.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and alum in mixing bowl. Add vegetable oil and boiling water; stir vigorously.
Dough should not stick to side of bowl.
Add food coloring and knead into dough until color is well blended.
Makes 1 cup.

title: april's blueberry tundra cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stem berries; gently rinse, pat dry, sprinkle with sugar and set aside.
In a bowl, combine the flour, 1 cup of sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and grated rind.
Prepare a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour small amount of batter into pan to coat bottom.
Pour 3 cups berries on top of batter, then cover with rest of batter.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in lightly greased casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first nine ingredients and put in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Crush Ritz crackers and add 1 stick of margarine.
Mix together and put on top of casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: linguine with clam sauce(low-cal)
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan. Add garlic and saute for 3 minutes.
Add wine, clam liquid, oregano and pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cook for 5 minutes stirring constantly. Add clams and cook on low heat for 3 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until they fall apart.
Break chicken into bite size pieces and put into casserole.
Reserve chicken broth.
Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup and evaporated milk. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle dressing over top of mixture.
Heat broth and margarine and pour on top to moisten dressing.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Serves 6.

title: best-ever brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease or spray a 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar, water and butter. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until melted and smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, and stir well. Combine flour and soda. Blend into chocolate.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Bake 35 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into small bars.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise.
Stir in fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: italian broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli.
Cook and stir broccoli in olive oil until cheese is delicate brown.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: italian soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage and roll into small balls (unless you're using ground beef) and brown.
Drain meat.
Add all other ingredients to large pot.
Stir; bring to boil and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: slim quiche lorraine
directions: Have the pie crust at room temperature.
Remove it from its pie pan and put it in a straight-sided 9-inch nonstick round cake pan.
Press the pastry thinly to fit the pan.
Trim away and discard the excess pastry that overlaps the edges.

title: toll house cookies(makes 16)
directions: Cream
together
the
first 4 ingredients; beat in egg. Sift together and add the flour, baking soda and salt.
Spoon by tablespoons
into
paper-lined cupcake pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Mix 1 envelope of the gelatin with the steak sauce and 3/4 cup of the tomato juice.
Heat, stirring until the gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining tomato juice and pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
In top of double boiler, soften remaining gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Dissolve over hot water. Stir in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add lemon rind, olives, onion, celery and tuna.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put on top of jellied tomato.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with lemon wedges and sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: brazilian black beans
directions: Soak the beans in water overnight (or at least 2 hours).
Cook with bay leaf and green pepper until tender; discard bay leaf and pepper slice.
In another pot, saute crushed garlic and chopped onion until tender; add beans and mix thoroughly.
Cook 15 more minutes.
Serve with rice, collard greens and slices of orange for a balanced Brazilian meal!

title: pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed, except bacon, and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with bacon, fried crisp and crumbled.

title: three hundred dollar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk (also marshmallows).
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients; drop on wax paper.
Melt paraffin wax and butterscotch morsels over boiling water and drop in cookies to coat.
Cool on wax paper.

title: garlic and mustard crumbed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Tear bread into small pieces and process in a food processor until crumbs form.
Wipe any bread crumbs from the processor and put in the vinegar, parsley, mustard and garlic; process until all are finely chopped.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in a baking pan, pour the vinegar mixture over chicken, rubbing onto both sides.
Pat a thick coating of crumbs on both sides of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour until juices run clear when pierce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: john's red pepper jam
directions: Blend peppers only (with vinegar).
Keep using juice as blending.
Place in saucepan and cook until thick.	Add sugar, salt and can in quarts.

title: debbie coomb's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and pudding until well blended.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray pan or dish with non stick spray.
Dump pie filling in pan.
Crumble dry cake mix in top of pie filling.
Cut stick of butter into small slices.
Place on top of cake mix.
Top with pecans.
DO NOT MIX UP!!

title: spanish-style red beans 'n rice
directions: Put rice in a medium bowl.
Half fill with lukewarm water. Stir rice with your hands until the water clouds.
Pour off milky rice water.
Repeat and rinse rice 3 to 4 more times.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
Remove pie crust from freezer.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweet potatoes until smooth.
Mix in butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mix in nutmeg, salt and evaporated milk.
Place pie crust on preheated baking sheet.
Pour filling into pie crust.
Bake in center of oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Shake biscuits in cinnamon and sugar. Place in Bundt pan. Stir together the brown sugar, oil and whipping cream. Pour over the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Let sit 15 minutes. Invert pan.

title: honey chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cornstarch and cocoa, blending well.
Add water and honey, stirring, until blended.
Then cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Makes 1 1/4 cups sauce.
Refrigerate.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O, then add the 3/4 cup cold water. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add all other ingredients to Jell-O mixture and pour into slightly oiled 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
A dash of horseradish added to mixture gives a little more zest.
Serves 12.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Finely chop 1/2 cup pecans; reserve remaining pecan halves for garnish.
Into large bowl, measure chopped pecans and remaining ingredients.
Knead until mixture holds together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Between 2 sheets of waxed paper, roll half of dough 1/4-inch thick.
With 2-inch flower-shaped cookie cutter, cut dough into rounds.
With pancake turner, place rounds 1 inch apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a reserved pecan half into each. Bake cookies 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool cookies slightly on cookie sheet; carefully remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Repeat with remaining dough, trimmings and pecans. Store cookies in tightly covered containers.
Contain 70 calories each.
Yields about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.
Time:
About 2 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor and blend 5 to 6 seconds or until mixed.
Drop by tablespoons into hot, greased frying pan.
Turn when bubbles appear on surface and cook one minute more.

title: green chili and eggs
directions: Beat eggs with spices and oil slightly.
In casserole, make layers beginning with chilies, egg mixture, onion and cheese. Bake in 325° to 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Saute almonds in margarine until golden, then add the lemon juice and pinch of salt.
Heat the beans and pour mixture over.

title: holiday punch
directions: First, empty sorbet into large punch bowl.
Second, pour in can of orange juice.
Third, pour in Sprite and ginger ale.
May foam at top but it's okay.
Stir until sorbet has completely melted.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar, zucchini and maple flavoring. Set aside.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spoon into 2 small loaf pans or 1 large loaf pan, well greased. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: sweet potato-pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together until light and fluffy. Combine sweet potatoes, eggs, corn syrup, vanilla and pecan halves, mixing well. Add sweet potato mixture to creamed mixture. Pour into pastry shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Blend thoroughly; spread over crust.
Combine both puddings and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Spread over layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with pecans and grated chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: In skillet over medium heat, saute mushrooms in butter for 3 minutes or until limp.
Stir in peas, breaking apart.
Cover and steam for 4 minutes or until peas are tender.
Stir in chicken, pimento and pepper. Keep stirring and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted and blended.
Serve over patty shells, biscuits or noodles.

title: pop corn deer
directions: Mix Creole seasoning, pepper and flour in 1-gallon Ziploc bag; salt to taste.
Place deer meat in mixture and shake; remove and place in deep frying pan with hot cooking oil.
When meat rises to top (3 to 5 minutes), remove, drain and serve.

title: best macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Combine cheese, egg, milk, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in macaroni.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter chocolate pinwheels
directions: Cream butter, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Melt chocolate chips over warm water; cool slightly.
Roll dough until 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with chocolate.
Roll like a jellyroll; chill for 1/2 hour or more.
Slice about 1/4-inch.
Put on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil and drain spaghetti.
Brown hamburger.
Drain grease. Combine and mix above ingredients.
Add tomato juice until mixture is soupy.
Put in a baking dish (13 x 9-inch) and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Cut into squares to serve.
Reheat leftovers in microwave oven. Tastes great.

title: "quick" tomato vegetable soup
directions: Combine these 3 "cans" and heat to boiling.
This is quick and easy and tastes as good as homemade.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pie dough for 2-crust pie.
Spread rhubarb over the bottom of crust.
Mix flour, sugar and salt; then add beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350°.

title: brownie pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl, except the nuts, and beat with an electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Add the nuts and spread in a buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: lilac potpourri(here's another sweet smelling recipe.)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Seal tightly in a jar or Tupperware container, and let set for a few days.
Shake ingredients, and potpourri is now ready to use!

title: baked lentils
directions: Cook lentils.
When tender, place in baking dish and add tomatoes.
Saute pepper and onion
in oil.
Add all ingredients to lentils, plus salt (if lentils were not salted during cooking). Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 1 cup measuring cup.
Add enough Pet milk to make 1 full cup.
Add this mixture to 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour in large mixing bowl.
Mix well until dough consistency. Next, roll out very thin and cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Saute carrots, onions and celery in butter until tender. Cook potatoes in chicken broth.
Add carrots, onions, celery and ground beef to broth.
Make white sauce and add to thicken.
Add cheese, basil and parsley.
Heat to melt.

title: perogie casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Slice and fry small onion in melted stick or margarine.
Add the cheese to the potatoes; cover and let cheese melt in the potatoes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, place half of the noodles.
Add the potatoes and cheese and then top with the rest of the noodles.
Pour butter and onions over top.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mollica's horseradish cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and melt in microwave.
Pour into plastic container while warm.
Let cool; then cover and refrigerate.
This keeps several weeks.
Serve with any crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions on package with the chopped onion.
Mix in rice, cheese, milk and water from the broccoli.
Place in baking dish.
Put Durkee onions over the top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday cake
directions: Mix in order and beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: sherry's pork chop casserole
directions: You will need 10-inch square dish (ovenproof).

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender. In a large bowl, combine stuffing and beef bouillon. Add all but the last 2 ingredients. Mix lightly until well blended. Shape into a loaf and place in a shallow baking pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with oregano. Continue baking 30 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese according to directions.
Add tuna and peas.
Stir well.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together and pour over cake mixture.
Cook 45 minutes until light brown.

title: no-cook mint divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix, corn syrup, extracts, food coloring and boiling water in small bowl of electric mixer.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form, about 4 to 6 minutes.

title: spicy cider
directions: Pour cider or juice into a saucepan.
Add candies.
Cook over medium heat.
Heat until candies melt.

title: sissy's chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and chili pepper.
Mix together with beans, tomatoes and dry ingredients.
Stir together.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients quickly.
Quickly drop in mounds onto wax paper.
Store in sealed container.

title: deep dish pizza casserole
directions: Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and the pizza sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes. Prepare pizza dough as directed on package.
With greased fingers press dough onto bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half of the meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat with remaining meat sauce and cheese.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chili chicken stew
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and cook chicken and next 3 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned. Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Top individual servings with garnishes as desired.

title: scrapple
directions: Combine meats and broth; heat to boiling.
Add seasonings. Stir in corn meal slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook 30 minutes; add cayenne.
Pour into pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in thin slices and fry.

title: potato chowder
directions: Peel
potatoes
and dice.
Soak in cold water.
Fry ham and onions
together until nicely browned.
Drain diced potatoes and place layer in bottom of stew pot.
Add layer of ham and
onions then
sprinkle with parsley.
Repeat layers until all
is
used. Cover completely with water.
Bring to boiling point
over
medium heat
and cook until potatoes are tender. Add
milk,
salt
and pepper.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cooke & stire ground beef & onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer 10 minutes uncovered.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Combine 2 teaspoons sugar and cornstarch in water in glass measuring cup.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring every 20 to 30 seconds until mixture is clear and thick.
(Watch closely in microwave so it doesn't boil over.)
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until soft peaks form. Gradually, add remaining sugar.
Stir in cornstarch mixture gradually and beat until meringue stands in stiff peaks.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Whip bananas until light.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to first mixture. Add nuts, bananas and lastly chocolate chips.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine jello's dry.
Follow directions on box to make jello. Slice bananas into jello.
Add drain pineapple (reserve juice). Add marshmallows.
Mix together and pour in 13 x 9-inch dish to congeal.
Place in refrigerator.
Mix reserved juice, flour, butter, beaten egg and sugar.
Cool over low heat until thick. Cool.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over jello.
Top with nuts.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss with any assortment of chopped vegetables and refrigerate.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in crust; dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° until a silver knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, pumpkin and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, nutmeg and salt.
Mix egg mixture with flour mixture.
Mix well.
Fill 4 well buttered coffee cans 1/2 full (1 pound cans).
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool in cans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add all ingredients in large pot.
Boil until butter melts well.

title: figato(baby beef liver)
directions: Cut liver into strips and set aside.
Chop onion into medium pieces or you can slice.
Saute onion in a frypan with oil and butter.
Dip liver strips into flour; add to onion mixture in frypan.
Should cook within 3 to 4 minutes.
When liver is cooked, top with sage leaves and serve.

title: pretzel-strawberry dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix jello with boiling water; add cold water and berries and chill until partially set.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip, then fold into jello mixture and pour over cooled pretzel crust.
Chill until firm. Enjoy!

title: cubed beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion and beef in oil until onions are soft.
Stir in soup, sugar and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in sour cream just until steaming hot.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot buttered cooked noodles. Serves 6.

title: super hobo beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet and let bubble a few minutes on stove.
Spoon generous helpings onto round sandwich buns.
Makes enough to fill 12 good picnic sandwiches.
A few pickles taste mighty good tucked in these too!

title: garlic roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; slice 1/4 inch thick.
Rinse in cold water; drain thoroughly.
Mince garlic and put through press.
Melt butter in small saucepan; add garlic and cook on medium heat for 1 minute.

Place potatoes in large bowl; add butter/garlic mixture, half the Parmesan cheese and seasonings. Stir until well coated; pour into greased shallow baking dish. Top with remaining cheese; bake at 400°, uncovered, until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Do not stir or turn while baking.

title: creamy doubledecker fudge
directions: In a 2 cup glass container with handle, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened milk.
Cook in microwave on 100% power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread evenly into foil lined 8-inch square pan.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Heat butter.
Add onion and saute about 4 minutes.
Add broth and cauliflower; heat to boiling point.
Add cream; do not boil. Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: no-cook candy
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put on board.
Knead until smooth and satiny.
Tint with food coloring, if desired. Make into small balls.
Roll in nuts.
Store in airtight container.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: supreme fudge
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup, combine first 5 ingredients. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir well until sugar dissolves. Microwave on High 9 to 11 minutes or until mixture reaches 234°. Let stand about 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook at medium setting for 8 hours.

title: barbie and bill's play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large cooking pan.
Stir over medium, then low heat until thick.
Knead on table until smooth.
Store in airtight container.
Have fun!!!

title: arlene's carrot cake
directions: Combine pecans and melted butter in shallow baking pan; stir to coat pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring twice. Cool; set aside.

title: rolls
directions: Spray pans.
Put frozen rolls in bottom of 9x13-inch or 9x14-inch pan.
Or, cut balls in half and put half in bottom. Cover with half of the mixture and repeat in bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bring butter and cup of brown sugar to boil.
Drizzle over frozen rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate. Enjoy!!!

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Form into rolls and put in freezer overnight. Slice rolls thin with sharp knife.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove and debone chicken.
Skim fat from broth and add water to bring to at least 3 quarts.
Add vegetables to broth and bouillon and canned broth. Cook until vegetables are about half done.
Add noodles.
When noodles are almost done, add chopped chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Add additional water and seasoning as desired.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour on top of rhubarb. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix
yeast
in
water,
mix
other
ingredients
except margarine, add yeast mixture.
Roll out like biscuits and cut, dip in margarine, place in pan and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water and sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over yeast when you put in cup.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Separate pieces of chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Melt fat in skillet and saute chicken; brown both sides.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Brown onion and garlic in the fat left in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place pieces of chicken on top of sauce.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove garlic clove.
Serve on hot platter with Mexican corn.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars. Add beaten eggs. Sift flour, salt and soda. Add to mixture. Stir in vanilla, chips and nuts.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes each pan full at 350°.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Boil chicken until well done; saute sausage and onion together.
Place chicken in a bread pan; place sausage and onion over chicken.
Mix in milk and then brown gravy and mix together. Pour over chicken; place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Add sifted flour and dry ingredients, then apples.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper; coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven; add soup, 2 1/2 cups
water,
onion,
basil, potatoes and carrots. Cover and bake in 350°
oven for three hours.
One hour before cooking time is up, add 1/2
cup
of red wine or water.
Stir; then return to oven.

title: raspberry torte
directions: Cream and blend together. Press dough into greased 10 x 15 jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Take out and spread 1 (12 ounce) jar of black raspberry jam or jelly on hot crust.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Slice angel food cake 3 times.
On bottom layer, put 1/3 of the strawberries, plus some juice.
Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Cover layer of cake with mixture.
Add next layer of cake, strawberries and Cool Whip mixture.
Add last layer of cake, strawberries and Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Eat!
Eat!
Eat!
Um Umm!
It's soooo good!

title: cabbage and cheese bake
directions: Put coarsely cut cabbage in greased casserole.
Stir in grated cheese and milk.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: holiday orange balls
directions: Mix crumbs, coconut and powdered sugar.
Add juice and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in additional powdered sugar.
Store in covered container overnight.
Makes about 3 dozen.
May have to refrigerate before making balls.

title: quick lentils and rice(child-approved)
directions: Cook the Progresso lentil soup according to the directions on the can. At the same time, cook the rice according to the package directions for 1 cup rice.

title: orange punch(for children or teetotalers)
directions: Beat orange juice with sherbet and ice cream.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and stir.
Serve at once.

title: kayla's favorite chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, oranges, salt and almonds.
Fold in salad dressing, whipped topping and noodles just before serving. Mix well.

title: fruit jar tomato relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables in layers in quart jar to make stripes of different colors.
Pour rest of ingredients over chopped vegetables.
Cover and chill 4 to 5 hours.
Turn over. Chill 4 more hours to marinate evenly.
Makes 1 quart.

title: rolls
directions: Place sugar, Crisco, and salt in a large bowl.	Pour scalded milk over this and let cool.
Then add 4 c. flour and mix well. Dissolve yeast in tepid water and add to flour mixture.
Add remaining flour.
Cover with greased waxed paper. Let rise until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Pour dough onto floured board.
Roll out.
Cut.	Dip in melted butter.
Place in pans to rise, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 30 rolls depending on size.

title: yellow squash cake
directions: Cream eggs, vanilla, sugar and oil together.
Add squash, flour, soda, salt, pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Stir together until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, vinegar and onion juice in the blender.
