On medium speed, add oil very, very slowly.
Blend until thick.
Add poppy seed and blend again.
Store in refrigerator. Great on grapefruit and avocado salad.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until blended.
Sift together flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk to the egg-sugar mixture.
Stir thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in melted butter.
Melt the 1 teaspoon butter in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet and thoroughly coat sides.
Pour batter into the warm skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until top just begins to brown.
Serve warm in wedges from the skillet.
Makes 1 corn bread, 12 servings.

title: chicken stew with dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Mix dough like pancake mix or thicker, drop by teaspoon into boiling broth until done.
Add a few drops of yellow food coloring for appetizing look.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa in saucepan.
Add small amount of water and mix.
Add remaining water.
Stir and bring to a boil. Cook one to two minutes to thicken slightly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Best when used warm on ice cream or other dessert.

title: japanese salad
directions: Prepare 1 day ahead of use.
Bake chicken breast, unseasoned, skin side down, at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes (micro, 6 minutes). Dice.
Toast sesame seeds and almonds 10 minutes in 300° oven.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in 1 or 2 small oven dishes. Heat at 350° for 20 minutes or more until browned.
Serve hot with Fritos, crackers and veggies.

title: indian-style sweet potato patties
directions: Combine egg, jalapeno pepper, garlic, cumin, ginger and salt in a large bowl.
If necessary, place shredded sweet potato in several layers of clean white paper towel, firmly pressing to remove excess moisture.
Add sweet potato, corn, bread crumbs, spinach, green onions and cilantro (if desired) to the egg mixture and mix well.
Shape mixture into 12 two-inch patties.
Heat oil in 12 inch non-stick skillet over medium heat.
Cook patties in hot oil about 6 to 8 minutes, turning once. If desired, serve with mango chutney and yogurt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat orange roughy(low cholesterol and very tasty; serves 4)
directions: Heat most of the oil in a skillet.
Add fish and saute 2 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients except orange juice.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Use remaining oil to grease sides and bottom of casserole.
Put 1/2 of fish in casserole.
Add 1/2 of the onion mixture.
Layer with rest of fish.
Top with remaining onion mixture.
Cover.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly at 375°. Serve with rice.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Let Jell-O set, but not firm.
Then fold in pineapple.
Fold in rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: molded cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine and place in container of your choice; let set. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add cold rice to the dressing mixture, then the chicken, celery and nuts.
Fold in oranges a layer at a time.
They need to be in the salad for a while to marinate.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift the flour.
Add salt and sift again.
Add shortening using a pastry blender.
Cut into flour until coarse crumbs are formed.
In a small bowl or 1-cup container, beat egg.
Add water and vinegar; drizzle over flour mixture.
Mix until the flour is moistened and holds together in a ball.
Divide into 4 pieces. This will make four 9-inch single crusts or 2 double crusts.
If making pie shells, bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: two bean and rice salad
directions: Mix in a 2 1/2-quart container the first 8 ingredients.
Add dressing and toss gently.
Cover and chill for up to 24 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half. Remove yolks and mash with mayonnaise and sweet and dill relish. Spoon mixture into egg whites. Sprinkle with salt and ground red pepper (lightly).

title: apple bars
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: go-go shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container and process until smooth.
Yields 2 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil the chicken breasts.
Cook broccoli.
Remove from burner before time limit.
Put half of the soup on bottom of pan evenly. Take chicken from the bones in strips.
Put the strips over the soup, covering the bottom of pan.
Put the other half of the soup on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Put broccoli on top of soup with ends toward the end of the pan, flowers in the middle.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.
Put foil on pan; bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: upside-down lemon meringue
directions: Beat egg
whites
until
stiff,
gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar and
continue
to
beat
until glossy.
Spread in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in slow oven, (150°) about 1 hour until
dry.
Meanwhile,
combine the 2 egg yolks with 1 whole egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in a saucepan with juice
of
1 lemon and rind.
Cook over hot water until thick. Cool completely.
After	meringue
has cooled, fill shell 1/2 with whipped
topping.
Top
with
lemon custard and decorate with dollops
of whip cream and strawberry halves.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Let cool until syrupy. Beat in sour cream. Fold in pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: frank-macaroni medley
directions: In a pot, boil 1 quart water.
Add macaroni; boil 8 minutes until tender.
Drain macaroni.
Add milk, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole.
Split franks almost through lengthwise.
Cut in half crosswise.
Arrange franks on top of macaroni mixture.
Fill slits with chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Day 1:
Line pan with heavy foil.
Place brisket on foil. Pour 1/3 cup liquid smoke over meat.
Sprinkle with garlic, onion and celery salt.
Seal tight and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Add corn and halve the onions.
Mix well; pour half into greased baking dish.
Cover with a layer of grated cheese; then add the rest of the corn.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart glass measuring pitcher.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven 6 minutes on High; or until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in peanuts into mixture. Cook uncovered in microwave to hard-crack stage (8 to 10 minutes at High); stir twice.
Add baking soda and vanilla; mix well.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn and put in roasting pan (disposable type).
Melt margarine and add brown sugar, salt and Karo.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda. Pour over popcorn and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix jello.
When jello sets, cut in small pieces.
Cut apple and banana in small pieces.
Drain liquid from fruit cocktail.
Mix jello pieces, apple, banana and fruit cocktail together.
Add marshmallows and small Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: noodle-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and
onion.
Cook noodles until tender, drain. Combine all
ingredients
in
greased
casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm.
Good with Melba toast rounds or Bremner wafers.

title: nutty cheese bars(quick and easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: baked beans
directions: For each can of beans used, dice three strips of bacon and fry. When almost done, add some chopped onion.
After onion starts to brown, pour off almost all the grease.
Add the beans, one tablespoon of brown sugar and three tablespoons of ketchup.
Stir well, cover and simmer slowly 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican soup
directions: Saute and drain ground turkey and onion.
Add (juice included) pinto beans, jalapeno pinto beans, white hominy, yellow hominy, Ro-Tel tomatoes (cut up), 3 cans water, taco seasoning and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing (original mix).
Simmer approximately an hour.
Serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice pork or bacon and saute in pot.
Add onion (I use more onion than recipe calls for) and cook until tender.
Add potatoes and water and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add the corn, seasonings and scalded milk.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, beat together butter and cream cheese.
Stir in the remaining ingredients (except French fried onions).

title: sandy's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain; place in casserole dish. Pour Cheese Sauce over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until bubbly. Let cool for 1/2 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat milk. Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup of milk and add beaten egg yolks. When warm, mix all together and cook until thickened. Add coconut. Put in baked 9-inch shell.

title: potato salad ii
directions: Peel, wash and dice potatoes.
Boil until tender, about 30 minutes; drain.
Add margarine, salt and pepper to hot potatoes. Mix in a bowl the eggs, onion, pickles and juice, pimento, mustard and mayonnaise.
(This can be mixed an hour or so ahead of time and refrigerated.)
Add mixture to potatoes while they are hot or very warm; mix gently.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Put rice on to boil for 10 minutes, then add soup and broccoli to onion.
Cook low until broccoli is tender.
Add Velveeta; mix until it is melted.
Add rice mix and then pour into a baking dish.
Cook in oven at 350° about 10 minutes, then serve.

title: phil's famous fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Combine flour, rosemary, thyme, seasoned salt, pepper and salt.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken; cook until golden brown.

title: corn chowder with red potatoes
directions: Melt oleo.
Add ham, onion and celery.
Saute about 10 minutes.
Add thyme and potatoes and cook, stirring.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add corn and milk and heat until simmering.

title: lemon chicken(a definite lemon flavor)
directions: Pound each chicken breast half to an even thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Over medium heat, brown chicken lightly on both sides.
Remove chicken.
To the pan, add the broth and wine; bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, squeeze 1/4 cup juice from one of the lemons.
Combine juice and flour until smooth.
Add to skillet; cook until thickened, stirring frequently.

title: herbed lamb chops
directions: Combine wine, lemon juice, oil, garlic, sage, rosemary and oregano in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Trim excess fat from chops.
Place chops in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, turning chops occasionally.
Arrange chops with thickest portions towards outside of dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at Medium (50%) power for 8 minutes, turning chops over and rearranging after 4 minutes.

title: eggplant balls
directions: Cook eggplant and potatoes in pot until soft, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain water, mash vegetables; allow to cool.
In large mixing bowl, put mashed vegetables and add egg, cheese, parsley, garlic and enough seasoned bread crumbs to form mixture that holds its shape.
With hands, form balls and drop into hot oil and brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a percolator bin.
Pour juice in percolator pot.
Perk until heated.

title: melba sauce
directions: Mix and cook over low heat until clear.
Strain through a fine sieve and cool.
The addition of 1/2 cup currant jelly gives a sparkle to its color.
Serve over vanilla or peach ice cream or canned or fresh stewed peaches.
Excellent served over fresh fruit salad.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt cheese and butter in fondue pot.
Add crab meat--Enjoy!

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and eggs until creamy.
Add sugars, salt, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Beat until creamy then add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Put spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: beanee weanees
directions: Put pork and beans in saucepan.
Add franks (cut in small bite-size pieces) and barbecue sauce.
Cook on medium heat for 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly.
Add the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, spices and nuts; mix well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured bread pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar together.
Add molasses and shortening and mix this in well.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach cakes for strict fast
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Cut up into smaller pieces, add diced onion to spinach.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use your favorite bobalki dough recipe.
Roll out a small portion of dough at a time and cut into large squares.
Fill each square with about 1 tablespoon filling, fold over and pinch as you would for pirohi, being sure to seal the edges.
Prick with fork and brush with oil. Bake in well-greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Onto a piece of waxed paper, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Pour butter into mixing bowl. Add sugar. Stir until dissolved. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla; add flour mixture, beating well until smooth. Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips; spread into pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; cut into 3 1/2 x 2-inch bars. Makes 24.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Tear lettuce; place in deep bowl.
Layer other ingredients in order given except for sugar and mayo.
Add sugar to mayo.
Spread over top as you would frosting.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix all the rest of ingredients with the first 3.
Put in muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, checking until done.
Batter can be kept in refrigerator, covered, for at least 3 weeks.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine crumbs and melt butter.
Set aside 1/4 cup of butter crumbs.
Combine remaining crumbs, oysters, mushrooms, cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Turn into a baking dish.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.
(May omit mushrooms.)

title: sausage shop chilli
directions: Cook to suit taste.

title: mexican pizza party dip
directions: In a pizza pan spread softened cream cheese to make a "crust". Spread salsa evenly over cream cheese for "sauce".
Layer shredded lettuce and then shredded cheese.
Sprinkle with chopped green onion for color.
Serve with corn chips.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in 3 tablespoons of lard.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll the dough to 1/4-inch thick; spread with melted oleo, brown sugar and apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll and cut into slices 1 1/2-inches thick.
Place in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cutout cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Place in large mixing bowl along with butter, sugar, milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes.
Decorate.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire racks.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: biscuit tortoni
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold water in small bowl to soften.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat eggs in large bowl until thick.
Add sugar gradually and blend well.
Stir in milk, gelatin mixture, salt and flavoring.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Whip cream enough to hold soft peaks.
Fold into chilled mixture.
Pour into 8 to 10 paper cups.
Sprinkle crumbs on each and top with a maraschino cherry.
Cover well and freeze until firm.
May be kept frozen for some time.

title: mango broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli until crisp-tender. Drain and chop into bite sized pieces. Stir together next 3 ingredients; add broccoli and stir to coat all pieces. Add mango and nuts. Stir and chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Put oleo on top; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, sift together dry ingredients and set aside. In small bowl, beat eggs and oil. Add pecans and strawberries. Add this mixture to dry ingredients, mixing until just well blended.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Rinse and de-stem all cranberries.
Place in pan.
Cover with cover.
Simmer slowly until softened.
Add sugar as cranberries cook.

title: pie crust for coconut cream pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in Crisco.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix with fork.
Press together to form ball.
Roll out on floured surface.
Gently fold and put into 9-inch pie pan.
Crimp edges.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool to room temperature or overnight.
Pour cold filling in crust.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chicken breast with shrimp sauce
directions: Place chicken breasts in roasting pan and cover with milk. Place 1/2 tablespoon oleo on each piece.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter or Crisco.
Add eggs, preserves, jam, buttermilk	and
vanilla.
Sift
together
flour,
soda, baking powder,
spice, salt and cocoa.
Add to flour mixture: raisins, nuts
and candied cherries.
Combine ingredients and bake
at 275° until done.
Line pan with waxed paper for easy removal.

title: eddie's peanut butter delight
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in cocoa until dissolved; stir in sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal until blended, then stir in peanut butter.
Drop by spoon onto heavy waxed paper or into a pan and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: bran pumpkin muffins
directions: Stir to combine Kellogg's Bran Bud cereal, milk, seedless raisins, pumpkin, sugar. Let stand 2 minutes to soften. Add to bran mixture and beat well egg and shortening. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg. Add to bran mixture. Stir only until combined. Fill greased 2 and 1/2 inch muffin pan cups 3/4 full. Sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake in moderately hot oven (400 degrees) about 30 minutes or until muffins are golden brown. Serve hot. Makes 12 pumpkin muffins.

title: oven rice
directions: Put all ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart covered casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and use as a dip or roll into a ball and roll in nuts.
Top with a cherry.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend sugar, margarine, shortening, eggs and flavoring together.
In another bowl, mix plain flour and soda together. Slowly mix buttermilk and flour mixture in with sugar mixture. Flour and grease pan.
Makes 2 to 3 cakes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix well to sugar.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
In large mixing bowl, add cake mix, oil and water; mix at least 3 minutes.
Add sour cream; mix.
Add butter, sugar and egg mixture; mix 1 minute.
Add poppy seed; blend.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° until meat is done, about 15 minutes.

title: fish stew
directions: Line the bottom of a large pot with bacon. Place a layer of potatoes over the bacon; then a layer of fish, in bite-size pieces; then a layer of onion slices, without separating the rings; and finally salt and pepper. Repeat layers, not including bacon, and finish with a final potato layer. Top with the chowder and crushed tomatoes. Can add 1 small can of tomato paste if you like a little more tomato flavor. Pour in enough water so that all is covered. Cover and simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour; bring heat back to a boil. Crack eggs into pot. Cook until eggs are done. Serve with crackers and hot sauce.

title: marshmallow cookie pops
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together in pan.
Put toothpick into each marshmallow.
Dip marshmallows into chocolate mixture, coating well.
Roll in cookie crumbs or chopped nuts.

title: nonedible cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine the ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat well until the dough is smooth and holds together well.
If the dough is too sticky, add a little more cinnamon until it reaches the consistency you like.
If the dough is too crumbly, add a little more applesauce.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add eggs, oil and can of fruit cocktail (do not drain).

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat drained juices and use to dissolve gelatin.
Cool and add Coca-Cola.
Chill until thick.
Stir in cream cheese, fruit and nuts.
Chill until set.

title: italian spice
directions: Place in a sealable freezer bag and freeze.
It preserves flavor better than drying.

title: pat's cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in mixer bowl and let stand until softened.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce and blend on low speed.
Beat until fluffy, scraping bowl often.
Cover and chill 8 hours or more. Shape mixture into a ball; roll in parsley flakes to garnish. Chill 2 hours until firm.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix and cook over very low heat until it forms and is not sticky to touch.
Knead like bread dough for a couple of minutes, until it is formed into a ball.
Store in airtight container.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Spread over tortillas; roll to enclose filling.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Chill for several hours; cut into 1/2-inch slices. Serve with salsa.

title: deviled eggs(makes 12 deviled eggs)
directions: Mix egg yolks,
mayonnaise,
vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Mix
with mixer (makes mixture real creamy). Add to your split egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika on top.

title: holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixing bowl.
Cream at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat thoroughly after each.
At low speed, add flour and extract.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mark off 20 squares and place one heaping tablespoon of cherry pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift confectioners sugar over cake.
Cool. Cut into squares.
Can also use lemon or blueberry pie filling.

title: sesame chicken and asparagus pasta
directions: *Toast sesame seed in 350° oven only 2 to 5 minutes.
Watch!

title: mint salad frozen
directions: Sprinkle dry lime Jell-O on crushed pineapple.
Stir well and add small marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator 6 to 7 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Shave, crush or blend one package of butter mints. Whip one pint of whipping cream or 2 packages of Dream Whip.
Fold whipped cream and the crushed mints into Jell-O mixture.
Place in an oblong pan and freeze.
Serve frozen.
Will keeps 2 weeks in freezer.

title: festive corn custard
directions: Butter a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickle relish
directions: Set the onions, cucumbers and peppers in salt water for 3 hours (1 gallon water to 1 tablespoon salt).
After 3 hours, drain off liquid and rinse good.
Bring the sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed to a boil.
Add other mixture; bring to good boil.
Seal in jars.

title: spiced cranberry relish
directions: Chop or finely grind the cranberries and orange. Mix all ingredients together. Let stand at least 24 hours in refrigerator to allow flavors to blend. Will keep in glass jar in refrigerator indefinitely. A real compliment to chicken or turkey.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, Wesson oil and pepper in water in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 3 to 4 minutes; cool.
Mix in large bowl corn, peas, beans (all drained), pimento, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Stir in cooled liquid; refrigerate.
Will keep for days.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.

title: noel bars
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add powdered sugar and melted oleo. Add dry ingredients.
Add fruit and nuts (chopped).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread with butter and powdered sugar frosting.
Cut in 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: beef tips
directions: Cover stew meat with water.
Cook in pressure cooker about 20 to 25 minutes; drain.
Place meat in crock-pot.
Cover with cream of onion and cream of mushroom soups.
Cook on high for about 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: italian squirrel
directions: Inspect squirrel, making sure all buckshot has been removed. Put cut up squirrel, berries and 1/2 cup salt in a non-aluminum bowl and cover with water.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swedish almond cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, baking powder and almond extract.
Mix very well until batter is smooth.
Pour in round cake pan; sprinkle almonds on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: out of this world candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and wax.
Set in refrigerator; chill.
Shape in small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together in microwave.
Dip balls in melted chocolate and set on wax paper until hardened.

title: microwave-mexican casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and green pepper in 2-quart casserole. Cover and cook on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook on High 2 1/2 more minutes. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Stir to mix. Cover and cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir. Cook on 80% (reheat) 5 minutes. Stir. Sprinkle broken taco chips on top.
Leave cover off.
Microwave on 80% (reheat) 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: batter pancakes
directions: Combine in a bowl and beat until light.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: chili hominy
directions: Drain and rinse hominy and set aside.
Saute the onion in the shortening in a large pot or skillet until tender.
Add the hominy and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add garlic and chili.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Put in casserole pan.
Add cheese until it melts.

title: sloe comfortable screw
directions: Build in Collins glass with cubed ice.
Fill with orange juice.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread over baked pretzels.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Allow the jello mixture to set quite a bit, then pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: easy to do donuts
directions: Place dry ingredients in a medium bowl.
If you use muffin mixes that have canned fruit, drain the fruit before you add it to the eggs.
Add eggs to the dry mixture.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick; cut out donuts and fry about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until brown; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cold soap
directions: Mix all together and stir until thick as honey.
Let stand until cold.
Cut into squares.

title: best ever strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool.
Add fruits and nuts.
Pour 1/3 mixture into 9 inch x 13 inch glass dish.
Cover remaining mixture and leave at room temperature.
Prepare cheese cake filling according to package directions.
Spoon cheesecake filling over gelatin.
Top with remaining gelatin mixture.	Chill until firm.
Serves 15.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Brown chicken and add rest of ingredients. Thicken with cornstarch.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well before stirring in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and water in mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Mix strawberries and dry gelatin in bowl.
Sprinkle marshmallows in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour batter over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Invert on serving plates.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: italian oven fried chicken
directions: Wash fryer; dip in oil and roll in bread crumbs to which the other ingredients have been added.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until browned.
If using boneless, skinless chicken breasts, bake for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken in serving pieces.
Cover with water and add salt to taste and butter.
Cook until tender.
Mix flour and salt; add broth and mix well.
Roll out very thin on a well floured board (just thickness of dime).
Cut in strips about 1 inch wide.
Leave surplus flour on strips of dough and drop in boiling broth.
Cover and let simmer 5 minutes.
Pepper to taste between layer of dumplings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well and then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: *Save out 6 tablespoons juice.
Use rest of juice.

title: fish fillets baked in shrimp sauce
directions: Put fish in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Use a shallow baking pan.
Put in 2 tablespoons of water.
Layer remaining ingredients with soup last and cheese on top.
Prepare 1 day ahead.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour

title: german cole slaw
directions: Combine and let stand while you make the dressing.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Melt butter and mix with sugar, then flour.
Dough is dry. Oil and flour baking dish or small spring-form pan.
Flatten dough in pan and refrigerate for one hour.
Do not refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
Check in 30 minutes and 10 to 15 minutes thereafter, don't let it get too brown on top.

title: honey-wheat muffins
directions: Combine flours, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk, oil and honey.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes a dozen muffins.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and line with graham crackers. Mix together pudding and milk; fold in whipped topping.
Pour half of mixture over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers over this and pour the rest of the pudding over crackers. Lay a third layer of graham crackers on top of pudding.
Frost top with fudge frosting and let set all day or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: pink grapefruit and pineapple punch
directions: Place drink mixes in large punch bowl.
Add water and pineapple juice; stir to dissolve.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Serves 29.

title: wams baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg until foamy; stir in milk and vanilla.
Cut each slice of bread in half.
Dip bread halves into egg mixture, turning to coat sides (not soak)! Measure and pour corn flake crumbs onto a plate.
Coat bread evenly on both sides with corn flake crumbs and place in single layer in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking cake pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in oven approximately 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve with jelly, maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place all cheeses into small bowl until soft.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce and blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy.
Cover; chill at least 8 hours.
Shape into 1 ball and roll in parsley.
Place on plate.
Cover and chill another 2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13 inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add undrained strawberries and pineapple.
When cooled to room temperature, add bananas. Turn a third of mixture into a mold.
Chill until firm.
Spread Cool Whip over congealed layer.
Add remaining mixture and chill until firm.

title: ham, eggs and cheese souffle
directions: Run cheese, ham and crackers thoroughly in food chopper.
Add worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, and milk.
Add eggs and baking powder.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add oleo to rice.
Add all remaining ingredients to rice in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash until tender. Drain. Mash. Add other ingredients and mix. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: asparagus, gruyere and tarragon souffled omelet
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, simmer the asparagus in water to cover for 3 to 5 minutes or until it is just tender.
Drain the asparagus, rinse it under cold water and pat it dry with paper towels.
Cut the asparagus crosswise into 1/4-inch pieces and transfer the pieces to a bowl.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Glaze:
Bring water to a boil.
Mix 2 cups sugar and cornstarch together and add to water.
Cook until clear.
Add Jell-O; set aside.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add pecans, flour, vanilla and potato chips.
Roll in small balls.
Take a small glass rolled in sugar and mash cookies.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: best baked beans
directions: Brown onion and bacon together; drain off grease.
Drain each can of beans slightly; combine all ingredients and bake for 2 hours at 350° in covered casserole.
Remove cover for last 30 minutes (or longer if drier texture is preferred).

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Blend dry ingredients; stir into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a well-greased 8-inch by 8-inch by 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Tenderize meat; salt and pepper.
Coat with flour.
Beat 2 eggs with 2 tablespoons water in deep plate and coat the cutlets thoroughly and then in bread crumbs.
Press bread crumbs onto the meat and shake off excess crumbs.
Heat oil or butter in frying pan and cook meat on both sides for 2 minutes, creating a nice golden brown crust.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with potatoes and salad.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Slice onions and potatoes.
Place ground beef, potatoes, onions, cream of mushroom soup and cheese in a casserole dish.
Make sure to put ingredients in layers in casserole dish.
Cook in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done; some ovens may vary.

title: 15 minute beef stew
directions: In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat and brown steak.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered 10 minutes or until steak is tender.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pacific chowder
directions: Cook bacon, drain, reserving fat, and crumble.
Cook onions and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat until tender.
Add soup, milk and dash of salt.
Heat to boiling.
Drain tuna and break in chunks.
Stir into soup mixture with half the crumbled bacon.
Heat through.
Dash with paprika.
Garnish with remaining bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical peach jam
directions: Mash bananas.
Chop cherries.
Chop peaches.
Combine mashed fruits and measure 3 1/2 cups into a large pan.
Measure sugar and set aside.
Place pan with fruit over high heat.
Add Sure-Jell and stir to hard boil.
Add sugar.
Bring to rolling boil for 1 minute, stirring!
Remove from heat, skim and ladle into glasses.
Add melted paraffin over top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix all together except nuts with wooden spoon.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator; keeps well or mold into football or basketball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with fancy crackers or Melba Toast.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute onion, celery, carrots and butter for 10 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir well and cool 1 minute.
Combine broth and half and half; stir into vegies.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and chicken.
Pour into casserole.
Top with Basic Pastry.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Let nonvegetable ingredients come to a boil for 2 minutes. Pour over the chopped cabbage while it is hot.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Cover and stir 2 or 3 times during its refrigeration.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Put beef, onion, bell pepper and celery in a Dutch oven; cover and steam over medium heat until the meat turns white.
Stir occasionally, breaking meat up with a fork.
The meat may be mashed fine or left in bite-size chunks, as desired.
(To reduce the fat content, drain the meat mixture at this point.)
Add tomatoes, beans, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, pushing cabbage under the liquid.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Adjust seasoning.
This freezes well and gets better every time it is warmed over.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Fry onions, garlic, parsley and bay leaves in olive oil, until onions are browned slightly.
Add meat and continue to fry until the meat is well cooked.
Force tomatoes through a colander to remove seeds.
Combine strained tomatoes with tomato paste, water, soda and seasonings and add to meat.
Cover and simmer for about 3 1/2 hours.
Add cheese and continue cooking 1/2 hour.
Serve very hot over spaghetti.

title: donna's homemade peach cobbler
directions: Note:
Any fruit pie filling will do.

title: scalloped potatoes(serves 50 people)
directions: Scrub, boil
and
cook potatoes.
Peel and dice.
It is best to make
white sauce for 10 pounds of potatoes at a time: So melt in	a
saucepan
one cup of margarine and blend in one cup of flour
until
smooth.
Stir
in
2	quarts of milk and continue stirring until thick and bubbly.
Place approximately 10 pounds potatoes (diced) in
an 18 x 25 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with cheese, 1 to 1
pounds per pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.	One pan serves 25 people.

title: syllabub
directions: Mix the cream with 1 tablespoon of sugar and the grated lemon peel. Whisk until it forms stiff peaks. Gently stir in the wine. In a separate bowl beat the egg whites until stiff, add remaining sugar and beat well. Fold into the whipped cream. Spoon into small cups or glasses, chill for at least 1 hour before serving. Serves 6.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix the jello with 2 cups of hot water.
Add pineapple juice, sugar, almond extract, frozen lemonade and can of water.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add 2 bottles of ginger ale and frozen strawberries.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Break crackers into 4 pieces.
Mix all ingredients; let set overnight.
Fry by the teaspoonfuls in butter or oil.

title: cuernavaca casserole
directions: In a small mixing bowl, mix cornmeal, salt and soda.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Blend in cornmeal mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
To make chicken dressing, substitute chicken for squash.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Salt and flour pork chops.
Brown in a small amount of oil. Put all other ingredients in a casserole dish and place chops on top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chip beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all but pecan chips and parsley flakes with an electric mixer.
Place and shape into a ball.
Cover with pecan chips and parsley flakes.

title: pineapple cream cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until fluffy and smooth. Add mayonnaise; blend well.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Chill several hours and serve with crackers (Wheat Thins).

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat margarine, sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out and knead just until smooth.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Cook for 1 minute. Add Ritz crackers. Cook 1 minute more and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cover with crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Place cucumbers and onions in glass or plastic bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and let sit for two hours. Rinse with cold water.
In a bowl, combine sugar and vinegar. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and onions. Place in freezer containers and store in freezer for year-round use.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set fruit and juice aside. Sprinkle chicken with curry powder. In a large skillet, brown the chicken on both sides in oil over medium-high heat. Remove and keep warm.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: In 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer prunes, apricots and undrained pineapple.
Combine cherry pie filling, water and dry white wine.
Pour over fruit.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours until dried fruits are tender.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Place oil in 7 x 11-inch baking dish in preheated oven at 350°. Saute meat, onion and celery; add seasoning, corn and peppers.
(I use canned slices as those used on nachos.)
Set aside.
Mix meal, eggs and milk (this mixture should be thin).
Combine entire recipe and pour into heated oiled dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: oh so rich! coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, pierce heavily with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together.
Immediately pour mixture slowly over cake, allowing it to absorb.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut together. When the cake is cool, spread Cool Whip and mixture over the top. Refrigerate.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix and put in Bundt or loaf pan (I spray mine with a little Pam).
Refrigerate overnight, covered with foil.
When ready to turn out of pan or cake plate, set in a pan of warm water for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Makes it easier to remove.

title: oven beef stew(serves 6)
directions: Mix these ingredients in a casserole dish that has a tight lid.
Put the lid on and put the casserole in a 275°
oven.

title: vegetarian chow mein
directions: In a large skillet, heat first 4 ingredients.
Add celery, onions, bean sprouts, mushrooms, tofu and peas or parsley.
Cook, covered, just until crisp-tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cooked mixture and stir until thick.

title: burger bangles
directions: Prepare dressing mix according to directions.
Mix meat and milk.
Divide into 4 to 6 patties.
Flatten meat.
Put ball of dressing in center and wrap meat up around ball.
Put in casserole.
Pour soup, sauce and catsup over balls.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Cook rhubarb and sugar over medium heat. Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 to 8 minutes until rhubarb is tender.
Add pie filling; cook 10 minutes more. Remove from heat. Blend with hand blender or standard blender unless you prefer chunky jam. Add raspberry jello; stir.
Put in jars; cool.
Refrigerate or freeze.
(Will be runny until cooled.)

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces and cut cauliflower into pieces.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon and onion in large dish.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and cheese together; pour over salad.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly for 24 hours.
Uncover, toss and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crunchy caramel pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour, stirring in nuts and butter.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350°, stirring often.
Line pie plate with 3/4 of mix and drizzle with 1/2 caramel sauce. Fill with softened ice cream and top with the rest of nut mixture and caramel sauce.
Freeze.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: butter-nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Gradually add flour, milk and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil, flour, baking powder, salt and anise extract.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° until done. Mix water and confectioners sugar together to make a light paste. Dip cookies in paste and then in jimmies.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, blend butter with sugar, then stir in the yeast mixture and egg.
Add flour, stirring until just blended.
Store covered in refrigerator at least 2 hours before using, or up to 5 days.

title: sliced mushrooms with parsley
directions: Place the mushrooms and cayenne in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes, or until tender, stirring once. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: weight watchers dressing
directions: Mix well and pour over salad.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and ginger in small bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Heat a small amount of oil in bottom of wok.
Brown chicken for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add peas, water chestnuts, onions and mushrooms.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sauerkraut roll-ups
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix kraut with onion in skillet; add bay leaf, salt and pepper to cover.
Simmer slowly until tender, stirring occasionally.
Let cool.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Tear on perforation.
Place triangles with wide part toward you.
Place some kraut mixture on crescent roll, rolling up away from you. Place on cookie sheet, brush with beaten egg and bake 15 minutes at 350° or until golden.

title: punch(serves 125)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: hot beef macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 15 minutes. Drain. Meanwhile, brown meat in the butter, onion, salt and flour. Blend in the wine (wine is impossible to duplicate). Stir in chili sauce, diced green pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then toss with the cooked macaroni.
Fold in the cheese, reserving some for garnish.

title: western skillet rice
directions: Brown meat and stir in soup, water, rice, tomatoes and peas. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add more water if it gets too dry before done.
Top with cheese.
Cook on low until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt olive oil in Dutch oven.
Add paprika and mix.
Add beef chuck, cut into 1-inch cubes.
Saute meat until brown.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over the meat.
Pour 3 cups of water over the meat. Stir in the carrots and celery.
Add 1 can of chopped mushrooms. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add a little more water.
Add flour paste for gravy.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend sour cream, Miracle Whip and dressing. Mix well.
Then add other ingredients and chill.

title: peg's lasagna
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook noodles until tender.
Blend tomatoes and sauce in blender, then mix with hamburger and heat. Mix seasonings in with hamburger and sauce.
Mix Ricotta cheese and sour cream into hamburger and sauce; mix well.
Spoon a thin layer of sauce into bottom of large baking pan, then layer of noodles, then spoon sauce on noodles.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Continue layers until noodles are gone making sure the sauce is on top of last layer to keep from burning.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut each chicken breast into halves or thirds (depending on size).
Rinse under cool water; then dip each piece into a mixture of Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Coat well.
Fry in a shallow pan in oil until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in a baking dish and top with Provolone cheese.
Pour a thin layer of spaghetti sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer salad, onions, peas and celery in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix the mayonnaise and sugar well.
Spread on top of the cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits or salad toppings.
Refrigerate.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients together.
Drain 1 hour or longer.
Combine the vinegar, turmeric, sugar and celery seed with the cucumber mixture.
Cook until it turns color, then, while hot, put into pint canning jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Mix corn, eggs, onion, pepper and corn muffin mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Put sour cream by teaspoon on top, then sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Chop chocolate and melt with 1/2 cup water in top of double boiler over hot water, stirring occasionally.
Cool. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue beating until shiny, stiff peaks form.
Set aside. Beat remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar with butter until mixture is light in color and fluffy.
Stir in melted white chocolate.

title: coconut almond carrot ring cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar and oil at medium speed until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots, nuts, raisins and 2/3 cup of coconut.

title: dressed herring
directions: Boil vegetables until they are ready (you can boil all vegetables in 1 pan).
Boil eggs hard.
Peel skin from herrings, cut them along the spine.
Take all bones away.
Cut herring meat into very little pieces and always check for bones.
Put herring meat evenly over the bottom of a large dish.
If you like onion, you can put little pieces of onion on the herring.
Then spread mayonnaise evenly (thin layer).
Grind potatoes and make next layer of it.
Spread another thin layer of mayonnaise.
Use a fork to plane the layers.
Then goes carrots (grind, put, spread).
Then you do the same with 4 eggs and beets.
Spread mayonnaise on the beets and grind 1 egg on top to make the dish beautiful.
This salad must look like a cake.
Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: uncooked lemon pie filling
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks and lemon and beat until well mixed. Pour into pie shell and top with meringue made with 3 egg whites. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs and brown meringue at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pastitsio
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, salt and thyme.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook macaroni.
Drain and stir in egg whites and cheese.
Add to meat mixture and put in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: egg bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add milk and fat.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Bake in well-greased shallow pan in hot oven (450°) for 20 minutes.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans; place in large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimentos and green onions; set aside.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil in a heavy saucepan; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over vegetables. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: fast cabbage-roll casserole
directions: In large pan, mix all ingredients.
Add water to just cover ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables and rice are tender.
Pour in pretty casserole bowl and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: butter rolls
directions: Roll each biscuit out flat and spread with butter, then sprinkle with sugar and a few drops of vanilla flavoring.
Roll and place in a baking dish.
When all 10 biscuits are rolled, place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and sprinkle each roll with sugar. Scatter small amount of butter between rolls.
Cover with a quart of sweet milk and bake until bubbling and lightly brown.
Bake at 350° and serve warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put on top of potato mixture about 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate. Pour dressing on prepared salad, slaw, or vegetables just before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar, flour, milk and vanilla.
Pour over melted margarine. Empty can of peaches (juice included) on top of batter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and bake for 50 to 60 minutes in preheated 350° oven. Batter will rise to top during baking to make crust.

title: pomodoro sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in a large pan.
When done, add whole tomatoes from can (retain juice until later). Cook tomatoes until soft.
Add capers, salt and pepper to taste, basil and the remaining juice.
Cover and simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: carol's zesty chili
directions: Simmer on low heat for 2 to 3 hours or in slow cooker on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: party cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture; mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup candies; reserve remaining candies for decorating. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. After baking, some of the candies may be cracked. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Use one package pita bread.
Split each round in half and cut into wedges.
Spread with margarine or butter.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in oven on cookie sheet at 350° until crisp.
Makes a nice "cracker" for soup or dips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat milk and margarine.
Cool.
Mix flour, butter, egg yolks, milk, sugar and salt.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Pour into a 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan or baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate-graham icebox cake
directions: Whisk cocoa, sugar, water and vanilla in a large bowl until blended and smooth.
Stir in a large spoonful whipped topping, then fold in remaining whipped topping until blended.
Line a small cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Arrange 3 graham crackers, side by side in middle of cookie sheet.
Spread heaping 1/2 cup filling evenly to edges.
Repeat with 5 more layers of crackers and filling.
Spread sides with remaining filling.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until cake is soft enough to insert toothpick into each corner. Carefully wrap in plastic.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours; 12 is better.
Transfer to plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: (Dilute each can with 1/2 cup chicken broth.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and place in 7 x 11-inch buttered dish. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: whipped cream salad
directions: In large chilled mixing bowl, whip cream to soft peaks.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons sugar and whip to stiff peaks.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients in food processor and mix well.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in pecans.

title: vegetable beef dip
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer, except mayonnaise.
Blend mayonnaise by hand.
Serve with any fresh raw vegetables.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix sugar, milk and Karo syrup.
Cook until golden brown.
Add dates and butter stir until dates are dissolved.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Beat until stiff and pour on wet cloth.

title: low-fat fruited raisin muffins
directions: Combine bran, yogurt, milk, spread and egg product.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
In a bowl, blend flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in bran mixture just until blended. Stir in cranberries and raisins.
Spoon batter into 9 greased 3-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until done. Serve warm.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to about 252° on candy thermometer or until sugar mixture forms threads when lifted from the pan. Slowly add about 1/2 of the sugar mixture to the stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Return the sugar to the heat and continue to boil for about 7 more minutes.
Keep the egg mixture beating.
Add the rest of the sugar mixture gradually and continue to beat.
Add the vanilla.
It will get stiffer.
Add nuts, if desired, and immediately drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to dry somewhat before storing.
Keep in cool place, not refrigerator however.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Warm drained potatoes and butter.
Mash and add rest of ingredients.
Use mixer.
Place in baking dish.
Top with miniature marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: chow chow
directions: Sprinkle
cup salt over vegetables and let stand 4 to
6 hours.
Drain and wash.
Then add black pepper, 1 tablespoon salt and sugar or vinegar.
Then cook.
Add mustard seed if liked.

title: graham cracker roll
directions: Roll graham crackers fine (save some to use later).
Grind marshmallows, dates and nuts.
Put in bowl and add whipping cream (do not whip).
Mix all together.
Shape into 2 or 3 rolls.
Roll in leftover crumbs.
Wrap in foil.
Can be kept in refrigerator several weeks.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place potatoes, onion, garlic, and spices in a large baking dish. Toss thoroughly. Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove foil, cook 30 minutes more to brown. Yields 8-10 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Prick holes in pie shell and bake 5 minutes at 450°.
Remove from oven and cool while bacon is cooking. Drain bacon on paper towel and crumble into pie shell.
Sprinkle cheeses over bacon. Beat eggs with half and half, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour carefully into pie shell.
Bake 12 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes until custard sets and crust and filling are lightly browned.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of greased pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Spread pineapple over sugar.
Combine all other ingredients, reserving cherries.
Pack mixture lightly into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Unmold loaf onto heated platter and garnish with cherries and sprigs of parsley.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and pimento.
Add chopped vegetables; combine.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled bars.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: Pour 1/2 the dressing over pasta.
Add basil and parsley. Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Prepare vegetables.
Place in bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; place in refrigerator until ready to mix with pasta.
Add rest of salad dressing and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
You can refrigerate for hours after it is mixed if you wish.

title: oklahoma sunshine salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water and add drained fruit.
Cook egg, flour and sugar in drained fruit juice.
Add to jello mixture.
Cool and add whipped topping.
Chill until serving time.

title: fudge clusters
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter in milk.
Blend in frosting mix (dry).
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth and glossy.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
(Keep mixture warm, stirring occasionally, while making candies.)
Cool until firm. Makes 3 to 4 dozen candies.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in pan.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.

title: "the best" pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 5-inch bread loaf pan.
In a large bowl, stir together oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Sift together the flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add dry ingredients to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in cherries and nuts. Pour batter into pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes. Add other ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Hardens in 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Do not stir.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk; pour over butter.
Mix 1 cup
sugar and peaches in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and beet juice.
Blend well and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Drain beets.
Add to hot liquid.
Heat on medium heat thoroughly.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cook and serve over vermicelli pasta.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Take juice and mix with instant pudding; pour over fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar and corn syrup until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together and spread over Rice Krispies mixture.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: shrimp bites
directions: Lightly toast muffins.
Mix other ingredients and spread over muffin half.
Cut into quarters.
Put on cookie sheet and place in freezer.
When frozen, put in plastic bag and keep in freezer until needed.
Broil until cheese puffs up!

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and pepper slowly in hot oil until onions are transparent.
Add hamburger and fry, stirring constantly, until mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings; mix well. Put in large greased casserole; cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: wiener stew
directions: Chop dice wieners and vegetables.
Saute vegetables.
Add wieners, tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil; simmer.
Serve over cooked rice.
Link sausages may be substituted for wieners.

title: jackson salad
directions: Puree onion and vinegar in blender or food processor.
Blend in mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Continue to blend and gradually add oil in thin stream.
Blend until thick.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, cool and crumble.
Mix torn lettuce, artichoke hearts, hearts of palm, Blue cheese and bacon together in large bowl. Toss with dressing and serve.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces. Add onions, poppy seeds, noodles, almonds and chicken.
Combine sugar, salt, vinegar, oil and pepper to make dressing.
Mix well. Right before serving, pour dressing over salad and add chinese noodles.

title: whitney's favorite tenderloin
directions: Bake tenderloin at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine in medium bowl mayonnaise, buttermilk, cheese, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, dash of salt and black and red peppers.
Blend thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cracker Barrel cheese, pineapple and Dream Whip (mix as directed).
Chill until firm.
Very good.

title: summer cool pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and pineapple, add lemon juice, a small amount at a time until mixture thickens.
Mix well.
Add chopped nuts of your choice, mixing well.
Pour into the 2 baked pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle
fresh ground pepper on top. Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
In a skillet saute celery and onion in butter until onion is tender, not brown.
Remove onion and celery from butter.
Blend flour, salt and pepper into melted butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly.
(Save one cup for Hot Tarter Sauce, recipe follows.)
Combine rest of sauce with salmon, celery, onion and all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Let cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Pour Hot Tartar Sauce on salmon loaf and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Drain well.
Cool.
Mix other ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Makes a large cake.

title: taco dip or salad
directions: Microwave beef on high for 8 minutes.
Mix beans, salsa and taco seasoning.
Pour over beef and microwave another 8 minutes. Add cheese and return to oven.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Serve with tacos and sour cream.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up 6 slices of bread and put in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix together all remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot chow-chow relish
directions: Make paste out of flour.
Add vinegar and other dry ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until it thickens.
Add vegetables.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Then pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: silver nut cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add flour and eggs alternately.
Mix in all remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325 degrees for 2 hours.

title: jud's broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring the water and bouillon cube to a boil. Add the broccoli and carrot.
Cook according to the broccoli package directions and remove from heat.
Do not drain.
In a separate saucepan, melt the butter and slowly stir in the flour. Continue stirring while gradually adding the milk.
Stir in the cheese, soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add the broccoli mixture to the white sauce mixture and cook over medium to low heat until the soup is the desired thickness. Serves 6 to 8.

title: smoked turkey breast submarine sandwiches
directions: Use as much shredded cheese and onions as desired.

title: chicken divine
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Drain.
Cut chicken into small chunks.
Spread broccoli in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then add chicken chunks.

title: bow ties
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Add milk a little at a time and knead until dough is ready to roll.
Roll a small amount at a time.
Cut in strips (diamond shape).
Put thumb through dough and pull dough through.

title: brownie ring cake
directions: Dump and mix method by hand!
Put dry ingredients in large bowl first, then add sour cream, milk and eggs.
Mix all together. Put in Teflon Bundt pan (lightly greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, no longer.
Cool completely on rack. Turn out of pan.
Wait until ready to serve; sprinkle with powdered sugar, sifted very fine.
Enjoy!
tags: Betty Crocker coconut pecan frosting mix

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves and mix well.
Chill in a ring mold, lined with plastic wrap.
When ready to serve, invert onto a platter and fill center of ring with strawberry preserves.
Also place crackers on outside of ring.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown bacon and beef.
Drain.
Mix all together in large casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut crumb cherry pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add coconut and stir until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.
Bake pastry shell at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cook pie filling in a saucepan over medium heat just until hot.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle coconut mixture over filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: strawberry banerin
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups frozen strawberries.
Stir until berries thicken the jello and break apart.
Fold in Cool Whip.
With a whisk blend until smooth and light pink in color.
Chill 1 hour.

title: horseradish sandwiches
directions: Split the hamburger buns in half.
Mix and spread mixture over entire bun.
Broil 6 minutes or until meat is done.
Watch carefully as they cook quickly.
Makes 11 to 12 sandwiches using both parts of bun.
Can make ahead and freeze.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Cover a 15 x 11 x 1-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Lay soda crackers flat to fill pan.
Boil together for 1 minute the butter and brown sugar.
Pour over soda crackers.
Put into 400° oven for 3 minutes.
Take out of oven and put Hershey bars over top, spreading to cover.
Refrigerate until hard.
When hard, remove and break into pieces.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onions.
Drain well.
Add drained green beans, corn and tomato soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: In a large skillet, mix beef and sausage.
Cook over medium heat until browned.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is limp.
Drain off fat.
Line a 9 x 9 x 12-inch baking dish with 1/2 ounce of chilies.
Top with 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Add the meat and top with rest of chilies; set aside.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix the flour with baking soda. In separate bowl, mix butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla. Add eggs. Gradually add flour mix. Add chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°F.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spray each tortilla with Pam and warm in microwave.
Brown beef and add onion, chilies, garlic, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Mix salsa and beans.
Layer softened tortillas in 9 x 13-inch dish with meat, bean mixture and top with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with avocado salad or other favorite dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together well.
Chill before serving.

title: sugar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until it starts to boil.
Do not let it thicken on stove.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° to 400° until center is firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 375°.
Let sit for 15 minutes.

title: leah's strawberry bread
directions: Mix undrained strawberries, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into strawberry mix, reserving about 1/2 cup flour. Stir to blend thoroughly.
Stir nuts into reserved flour (this keeps them from sinking to bottom) and add to bread mix.
Stir well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and lightly floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done (insert toothpick into center, if no batter clings to toothpick, bread is done).
If top starts to over-brown before done, loosely put a tent-shaped piece of foil over loaves.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, black pepper and 1/2 cheese crackers.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Cook 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Add sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: date nut cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add dates, sugar, salt and eggs. Mix and cook while stirring until it comes to a boil, then cook 10 minutes.
Take off heat, add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Roll into about 1-inch balls and roll in coconut to cover them.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Spread cherry filling in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix onto the filling.
Melt the butter; pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the top of all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix milk, cheese and onion.
Heat until cheese melts.
Layer spaghetti, cheese sauce and put tuna on top. Layer and use all of it up.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and add to boned chicken, soups, pepper and broth.
Layer Doritos and chicken mixture and cheese.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: margerite's maple frosted ritz's
directions: Add evaporated milk to mixture until desired thickness.

title: feta stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems (save).
Brush caps with melted butter.
Place hollow side up on baking pan.
Salt and pepper.
Mince the mushroom stems.
Saute the stems and chopped onion together in remaining butter.
Add garlic (crushed); combine stems, onion and garlic with Feta; mix.
Stuff caps.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tempura batter
directions: Mix until all is combined good.
Do not overbeat.
Keep batter cold.
(Can set bowl in a large bowl with ice to keep batter cold.)

title: fudge (2)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Cook slowly until it forms a soft ball.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream and beat until cool, then add nut meats.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Pour this hot over pickle rings in the large crock-pot and let stand overnight.
Do this for 3 days, reheating solution each day. On the fourth day, pack in hot sterilized jars.
Cover with hot syrup.
Makes 10 pints.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cut and cook cabbage in water until tender.
Drain.
Make white sauce using butter, flour and milk.
When white sauce is thickened, layer cabbage with white sauce alternately in greased baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry delight(sugar-free)
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package.
Pinch up angel food cake and add to mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Add cut up strawberries. Pour into oblong pie pan.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour; add egg.
Add milk gradually and mix well.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, powdered sugar and margarine together until softened.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend well.
Add rest of ingredients, one at a time, until a soft dough is formed.
Let chill in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with sugar.
Bake about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour in saucepan.
Add milk, egg yolks and margarine.
Cook to thicken.
Add vanilla.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together in bowl:
flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk and shortening; mix until smooth and add nuts. Turn into 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cocoa and pour hot water over everything.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix in a punch bowl.
Stir from bottom.

title: egg and ham casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Whip eggs with onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Pour over bread slices.
Cover with 3 cups milk.
Let stand overnight. Before baking, pour a little melted butter over all.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to a bowl, cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion and salt to chilled rice; mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.

title: connecticut beef supper
directions: Season meat and brown in oil with onions.
Drain mushrooms and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Stir liquid into meat.
Simmer until tender.
Put meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange potatoes on meat.
Mix soup, milk and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cranberry-mince pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven.
Preheat to 425°.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; add water.
Over high heat, cook and stir to boiling.
Add cranberries; return to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn mincemeat into 9-inch pie plate lined with pastry.
Top with cranberries.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits near center.
Seal and bake 30 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken in large pot; may add bouillon cubes if you like. Melt butter or margarine and slowly saute mushrooms and onions until onions are transparent.
Add to boiling chicken.
Slice potatoes (about 1 1/2-inch slices).
Add to chicken pot.
Slice carrots (1 to 1 1/2-inch slices).
Add to chicken pot.
Add 2 cups of white wine to chicken pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pot and turn heat on low.
Cook for 1 hour or until chicken is done and vegetables are tender.
